title: potato soup
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients until tender.
Add celery soup.
Cook until mixed well.

title: grandma's bread
directions: Cut bread into small diagonals, being careful not to slice all the way to bottom crust.
In saucepan, combine butter, mustard, seasoned salt, onion, poppy seed and lemon juice.
Stir until melted and blended.
Cut cheese into julienne sticks, about 3/4-inch long by 1/4-inch square.
Place cut loaf of bread on a large piece of heavy-duty foil.
Start in the middle, stuffing alternate sticks of Swiss and Cheddar cheese into diagonal cuts, tucking them deep inside the bread.
Use foil to hold loaf in shape as it expands from being stuffed with cheese.

title: chili, quick and easy
directions: Rinse the turkey and pat dry.
Rub cavities with salt and pepper.
Put some of the dressing in the neck cavity.
Pull the excess skin to the back and tuck under.
Fill the body cavity with dressing, then tuck the drumsticks under the skin at the tail. Twist the tip of the wings under the back.

title: easy clam chowder
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Heat and serve.
This is so easy and very good.

title: my aunt betty's hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt chocolate and water in top of a double boiler.
Add sugar and salt.
Allow to thicken, stirring frequently, 5 minutes. Remove from heat.
Stir in butter and vanilla.
Reheat when ready to use.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cook cake to package directions (2 layers).
Split cake layers open (4 layers) turn inside up to soak up icing.
Blend sugar, sour cream, and coconut.
Chill.
Spread
all but 1 cup between layers.
Blend remaining 1 cup with Cool Whip.
Spread on whole cake.
Store
in
airtight	container in refrigerator overnight.

title: eggless-milkless-butterless cake
directions: Mix together raisins, sugars, salt, water, oil, cinnamon, ginger and allspice in saucepan; bring to a boil and cook at a rolling boil about 5 minutes; cool to lukewarm.
Add baking soda; mix well.
Sift flour with baking powder.
Add flour and nuts to raisin mixture.
Stir until smooth.
Put batter in greased and floured pan (9 x 13-inches) in preheated 350° oven and bake about 1 hour and 15 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve when cool; uniced.
Serves 8.

title: turkey creole
directions: In an 8-inch skillet, cook and stir onion and pepper in oil until tender (about 5 minutes).
Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce, chili powder and salt.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Stir in turkey.
Heat and serve on rice.

title: grilled donuts
directions: Turn burner on to medium-high.
Place griddle on burner and let it get warm.
Put the donuts on the griddle just long enough to brown on both sides.
Put on a plate; add one scoop of ice cream.

title: mother's old fashion chocolate fudge
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar and salt in a large 3-quart saucepan. Add milk gradually. Mix thoroughly. Bring to a rapid boil on high heat, stirring constantly. Reduce heat to medium and continue to boil without stirring to 232° or until a small amount of mixture forms a soft ball when dropped into cold water.
Remove pan from heat; add butter and vanilla. Do not stir.

Allow fudge to cool at room temperature until it reaches 110°. Beat until fudge thickens and loses some of its gloss. Quickly pour and spread fudge in lightly buttered platter. Yield: Approximately 36 squares.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs till frothy. Add sugar and beat well. Continue beating, add 2 c milk. Heat on low, just till hot. Stir constantly. Pour egg mixture in freezer can. Cool in refrigerator for 1 to 2 hours. When ready to freeze, add evaporated milk, half and half, and vanilla. Stir; fill freezer can to fill line with milk. Put lid on freezer can and freeze according to manufacturers directions. To add fruit; puree first in blender, then add with evaporated milk.

title: jeneva's sweet pickle slices
directions: Take pickles out of the jar and rinse well.
Cut pickles into 1 inch slices and drain well.
Pour the juice from the jar and discard.
Put the drained pickle slices back into the now empty jar.
Add sugar, allspice, vinegar and cinnamon sticks.
Place the top on jar and store in the refrigerator.
Let sit for several days before eating.
Keep refrigerated.

title: hot and sour soup
directions: Cover the mushrooms with boiling water; soak 30 minutes. Drain.
Remove stems and shred.
Combine mushrooms, bamboo shoots, pork, soy sauce, salt and stock in large saucepan.
Bring to boil. Reduce heat and simmer 3 minutes.
Add bean curd, pepper and vinegar.
Bring to boil again.
Add cornstarch and stir until soup thickens.
Slowly pour the beaten egg into hot boiling soup while stirring gently.
Remove from heat and ladle into serving bowl. Stir in sesame oil.
Garnish with green onions.
Serves 4.

title: cherry cool whip salad
directions: Mix well and chill.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on box;
rinse and drain.
Grate the Cheddar cheese and save some chunks for top. Mix eggs, milk and cheese together. Add a little whole milk and mustard; mix with macaroni.
Bake for approximately 1 hour at 350°.

title: moose cookies
directions: Line a 9-inch square baking pan with waxed paper; set aside. Grind mints to a medium fine texture in an electric blender. Knead the butter into the flour until thoroughly blended.
Add the mints and continue kneading until dough is of a soft but solid consistency.
Pat dough evenly into prepared baking pan and refrigerate for 1 hour.
When removed from fridge, you cut pastry into 1-inch squares.
You may choose to imprint each square with a cookie press before sprinkling with granulated sugar.
Lift the waxed paper with the cookies intact and place the cookies about one inch apart on an ungreased baking sheet.
Place in freezer for 30 minutes.
During this 30 minute wait, preheat the oven to 300°. Bake frozen cookies 16 to 18 minutes.
These cookies should not brown at all.
Remove and cool on rack.

title: herb broiled tomatoes
directions: Place tomato halves in shallow baking pan and season with salt, pepper and marjoram. Top with bread crumbs; dot with 1/2 butter and sprinkle with parsley. Arrange mushroom caps, rounded side down, around tomatoes. Season with salt and pepper. Dot with remaining 1/2 butter. Broil 10 minutes or until golden brown. Invert mushroom caps and place one on each tomato half. Serve immediately.

title: banana dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender or food processor until banana is pureed. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.
Delicious spooned over mixed fresh or canned fruit.

title: crock-pot hen
directions: Place hen in crock-pot.
Pour dressing and syrup over it. Season with seasonings.
Lay bacon strips over it.
Cook overnight on low.
Serve with any side dish.
Pour heated liquid over hen to add flavor.

title: peanut butter marshmallow treats
directions: In large saucepan, melt margarine.
Add peanut butter chips and let them melt.
Remove from heat and add bag of marshmallows. Mix together.
Lay out long piece of foil.
Pour mixture onto foil, making a log shape.
Fold foil up on sides and ends of log. Refrigerate until hard.
Cut log in 1/2-inch pieces and serve. Quick and easy to make.

title: summertime bourbon slush
directions: Combine juice, ginger ale and bourbon.
Stir well and freeze until firm.
Break frozen mixture into chunks or scoop into tall glasses, filling 1/3 to 1/2 full.
Add carbonated beverage; stir until slushy.
Yields 4 1/2 cups.

title: cooked slaw
directions: From a small or medium head of cabbage, chop or shred enough to equal 1 quart.
Add the bell peppers, carrots and 1 tablespoon salt.
Soak this mixture for 1 hour, then drain.
Take the sugar, vinegar, 1/2 cup water and prepared mustard.
Let come to a boil. Let cool.
Add the celery.
Pour this mixture over the drained cabbage mix.
Put in jars; keep refrigerated.

title: fried catfish
directions: Wipe fish with damp cloth.
Mix flour, salt, pepper and cornmeal.
Roll Mr. Catfish in mixture and fry in hot Crisco until golden brown on one side.
Flip and brown other side.
Total cooking time is about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: applesauce date cake
directions: Cream shortening.
Add
sugar.
Blend well.
Add beaten egg and applesauce.
Rub dates with little flour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in
ring (tube) pan (greased).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: jello pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels and margarine together; spread evenly in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 7 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: old fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients; mix well. Drop from a teaspoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes, until cookies test done with a toothpick. Cool on cookie sheet about 1 minute, then remove from rack to finish cooling.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in water until tender.
Peal and mash (even better if sliced) with butter, salt and pepper.
Put squash in casserole. Mix together cream of chicken soup, sour cream and dressing mix. Pour over squash.
Bake at 350° for about 1/2 hour.

title: party mix
directions: Melt butter or margarine.
Add onion salt, celery salt, garlic salt, seasoned salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix with dry ingredients.
Bake at 250° for 45 minutes, stirring 3 times.

title: baked apples
directions: Peel and core apples.
Cut into large wedges.
Spray a small casserole dish with Pam and place cut apples into dish.
Sprinkle 1/2 c. brown sugar (more or less to taste) on top of apples. Sprinkle cinnamon to taste on top of apples.
Place 5 to 6 pats of butter in different areas, on top of apples in dish.

title: fluffy peanut butter dip
directions: In the freezer, chill a small bowl.
In a bowl, mix peanut butter, yogurt and cinnamon; stir with whisk, until thoroughly blended.
Gently stir in whipped topping; blend well.
Pour into small chilled bowl.
Chill in refrigerator before serving.
For dippers, cut apples or pears into wedges.

title: mocha toffee cheesecake
directions: Combine cookie crumbs and butter.
Press in bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Beat softened cream cheese with sugar, sour cream, vanilla and eggs.
Add chocolate and coffee to the cream cheese mixture.
Continue beating.
Sprinkle flour, 1 tablespoon at a time, over cream cheese and beat well after each addition.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Chop walnuts. Beat eggs.
Gradually beat in sugar, then oil. Combine dry ingredients.

Add to first mixture alternately with zucchini. Stir in raisins, walnuts and vanilla. Turn into 2 greased and lightly floured loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 2 3/4-inch. Bake on lower rack at 350° for 55 minutes until done.
Let stand 10 minutes. Turn out onto wire racks.

title: german spaghetti(a very old family recipe)
directions: Dice and fry bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon and fry onion and green pepper in bacon drippings.
Remove as much bacon grease as you like, leaving a little in for flavor.

title: jalapeno cheese potatoes
directions: In a skillet, saute the onions and pepper in 2 Tbsp. butter until soft.
Add the flour and then the milk, stirring until mixture thickens.
Add the onion mixture, pimentos and cheeses. Simmer until cheeses have melted.
In a lightly greased baking dish, place the potatoes.
Pour in the sauce and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: date filled cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening and add beaten egg and beat again. Add sifted dry ingredients and mix.
Roll dough out in a sheet 1/2-inch thick.

title: apple cinnamon puffs
directions: In a large bowl combine flour (1 cup), 2 tablespoons sugar, yeast and salt.
Add very warm water (120° to 130°) and oil.
Add egg.
Blend at low speed.
Beat 3 minutes on medium speed.
By hand add apples and remaining 1 cup of flour.
Spoon into 12 muffin cups.
Let rise, covered, for 1 hour (1/2 hour for quick rise yeast).
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Trim crusts from bread.
Spread with butter.
Arrange 6 slices buttered bread in greased rectangular 3-quart baking dish.
Brown sausage, stirring until crumbly; drain.
Layer half of sausage and cheese over bread.
Add remaining bread, sausage and cheese.
Beat eggs with milk, dry mustard and salt.
Pour over casserole.
Chill overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes, until set.

title: new england pumpkin pie
directions: Blend the first 6 ingredients.
Separate egg.
Beat egg yolk and add with 1 1/2 cups hot milk to pumpkin mixture.
Beat egg white and carefully fold into mixture.
Pour into a 9-inch pie shell.
Bake for 10 minutes at 450°.
Turn oven down to 350° and bake for 30 minutes or until firm.
Can top with whipped cream and/or chopped Brazil nuts.

title: breakfast sausage casserole
directions: Spray pan with nonstick spray.
Place croutons in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle cheese over croutons.
Brown sausage and drain.
Place on top of cheese. Beat eggs. Add remaining ingredients.
Pour over sausage.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sugarless apple dessert
directions: Combine gelatin, diluted apple juice concentrate, cinnamon and nutmeg in a large skillet, stirring well.
Let stand 1 minute. Cook over low heat for 1 minute or until gelatin dissolves.
Add apples.
Cover and continue to cook over low heat 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Stir apples gently and baste with pan juice several times during cooking process.
Add margarine; stir gently until margarine melts.
Remove from heat.
Cover and refrigerate until thoroughly chilled.
Spoon mixture into dessert dishes to serve.
A serving amount is 1/2 cup at 121 calories.
Diabetic Exchange:
1 1/2 starch.

title: egg custard
directions: Scald milk and butter just to bubbles.
Cream sugar, eggs and vanilla lightly and mix with first mixture.
Bake in 9 5/8-inch pie pan at 350° for 25 minutes or until center is set.

title: tv goo or chex mix
directions: Melt margarine in a large roasting pan.
Add the salts and Worcestershire sauce, then mix well.
Add remaining ingredients to the mixture, mix well.
Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 hours.
Stir every 30 minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook lasagne noodles in salted water; brown hamburger.

title: kao pad(thai fried rice)
directions: In a wok brown the garlic in the fat and add pork.
Pour egg over the pork, and garlic and stir quickly to the egg does not sit. Add soy sauce, crab and rice.
Stir well, tossing lightly.
Remove from heat and arrange on a serving platter.
Sprinkle with pepper to taste.
Garnish with green onions and slices of cucumbers.

title: cocktail wieners and sauce
directions: Combine ingredients, except wieners, in crock-pot on medium heat.
Add wieners.
Simmer on medium to high for 2 to 3 hours. The longer they simmer, the better they are.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Chop chicken breasts and place in casserole dish.
Add broccoli.
Melt cheese with soup in saucepan and pour over chicken and broccoli.
Crush crackers and place on top.
Pour melted butter over crackers.
Bake about 20 to 30 minutes until brown and bubbly at 350°.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and cottage cheese thoroughly.
Add Cool Whip and fruit.
Fold gently.
Chill for several hours.

title: blueberry banana bread
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Mix together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Fold in blueberries and bananas.
Put in greased bread pan.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed green peppers(microwave)
directions: Combine meat, water, egg, Minute rice, salt and pepper and about 1/8 of tomato sauce.
Wash and cut green peppers in half; remove seeds and membrane.
Fill loosely with meat and rice mixture.
Place peppers in a 12 x 7-inch flat utility dish.
Top with tomato sauce.
Microwave for 12 minutes, covered and on High (100%).

title: good tea
directions: In saucepan, add 2 cups water to tea bags.
Bring to a boil. Boil 5 minutes.
Remove tea bags.
Add sugar to hot mixture.
Stir until dissolved.
Pour in 2-quart pitcher.
Add water to 2 quarts. Add lemon juice.
Stir well.
Chill and serve.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Combine cheese, butter and half and half in a saucepan.
Heat until melted.
Pour over potatoes in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Let casserole stand for 1 hour.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Boil carrots until tender.
Peel carrots and wash. Cut into rings of medium thickness.
Cut the onion and bell pepper into rings (large onion and bell pepper rings may be halved or quartered, if desired).
Mix sugar, vinegar and vegetable oil in a large bowl. Stir well. Add other ingredients and stir until all are well coated.
Cover dish with a tight lid and turn often until marinated, for 3 hours or better still, overnight.

title: oven roasted potatoes
directions: In a large bowl, add all ingredients.
Stir until potatoes are evenly coated.
Pour mixture into shallow baking dish, stirring occasionally while baking.
Bake at 450° for 40 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Mix together pimento and cheese with a fork. If cheese is not soft enough, put in microwave for a few seconds. Add salad dressing for desired consistency. Add dash of salt and sugar to taste.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Slice cucumber and onions.
Mix all the other ingredients and pour over cucumbers.
Refrigerate.
Keeps several months.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Slice chicken into strips.
Slice onion and bell pepper. Slice carrots and prepare other vegetables.
Have ready to cook. In a hot skillet or wok, in hot oil, stir-fry chicken until browned (now is the time to add seasoned salt, if desired).
Add 1/4 to 1/2 cup sherry; let cook a little while.
Add vegetables. Stir constantly.
Add soy sauce to taste.
Don't let the vegetables overcook!
If anything, I like mine underdone so they are still crisp.
Serves 3 to 4 people.

title: turtles
directions: On greased baking sheet, arrange pecan halves, flat side down, in groups of four.
Center one caramel atop each cluster of pecans. Heat in slow oven at 325° until caramels soften, 7 to 8 minutes. Remove from oven.
With buttered spatula, flatten caramels.
Cool slightly.
Remove to wax paper.
Spread tops with melted semi-sweet pieces.
Let cool.

title: baked or grilled chicken
directions: In bowl, mix bread crumbs and spices.
Dip chicken in milk, then roll into spice mixture.
Place on hot grill.
Cook until tender, or bake in 350° oven for about 45 minutes.
Cover with foil to hold in moisture.

title: sausage balls
directions: Have ingredients at room temperature.
Thoroughly combine sausage, cheese and biscuit mix.
Form into small balls.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
These may be frozen and cooked later.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Put a layer of sauerkraut in the bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle onion and garlic powder over it. Top with sour cream; crumble corned beef over this.
Sprinkle cheese over beef.
Cube the bread and spread over the cheese. Melt the margarine and drizzle over the bread.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: crumb topping for fruit pies
directions: Mix ingredients together with a pastry cutter until crumbly.

title: beef roll-ups
directions: In a saucepan, saute onions in butter.
Add carrots, potatoes, 1/2 can of soup, parsley and 1/4 teaspoonful of dill.
Cook until partially tender.
Sprinkle meat with salt and pepper.
If using round steak, cut into 4 or 5 pieces and flatten.
Place stuffing in center of meat.
Roll up, tuck in ends and skewer with toothpicks.

title: easy banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and banana.
Sift flour, salt and soda together; add to mixture.
Add walnuts.
Pour into a greased 10 x 5 x 3 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour or until done in center.

title: lemon lush
directions: For 1st layer:
Mix together flour, sugar, margarine and nuts. Press into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until brown. Allow to cool.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: macadamia nut crunch
directions: Line
bottom
and
sides
of 9-inch round cake pan with aluminum
foil.
Butter
generously.
Cook nuts, butter, sugar and syrup
in
heavy
skillet
over
low heat, stirring until butter melts
and
sugar
dissolves.
Increase
heat and boil until mixture turns golden brown and begins to mass together, stirring constantly (about 5 minutes).
Pour into pan, spreading
evenly. Sprinkle
with
chocolate
morsels, let melt and spread evenly over top.
Cool 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and peel off foil. Cool completely and break into pieces.

title: milk chocolate fudge
directions: Put chocolate chips in top of double boiler.
Place over hot (not boiling) water.
Melt.
Add other ingredients.
Pour in pan.

title: mandarin orange salad (low calorie)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Leave in refrigerator for 2 hours before serving.
Use bowl that has a cover.

title: dumpling noodles
directions: Sift flour and salt in mixing bowl.
Combine eggs and water. Add to flour mixture and beat well.
Drop by teaspoonful into boiling salted water.
Cook for about 12 to 15 minutes or until dumplings float.
Drain and serve with melted butter.
Makes 6 servings.

title: enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat oil and then stir in flour.
Cook 1 minute.
Add and stir in chili powder.
Then add broth, tomato sauce, cumin, garlic powder and salt.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Stir-fry tortillas for 3 to 5 seconds on each side.
Place enchiladas in a pan and cover with sauce and cheese.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: mom's nut cake
directions: In separate bowl, mix flour, nuts and raisins. Cream butter, sugar, and the eggs, mixing well. Add to dry ingredients. Add vanilla to taste. Batter will be stiff. Bake at 350 degrees in tube cake pan for 1 hour 15 minutes or until done.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Beat eggs and sour cream.
Add oil and mix.
Add cornmeal, corn, peppers and 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese.
Pour in greased baking pan, sprinkle 1/2 cup shredded Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350° until golden brown.
I put more jalapeno pepper than it says.

title: toll house squares
directions: In a small bowl, put flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir with fork to mix up.

title: crunchy chicken cheese bake
directions: Place chicken in casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Mix soup and milk together.
Spread over chicken.
Combine butter and stuffing; sprinkle over chicken.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
Great served over rice.

title: jail house cake
directions: Mix all ingredients into bowl, including pineapple juice. Pour into greased pan, 9 x 13-inch.
Sprinkle top with one cup of chopped nuts and 3/4 cup brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: creamed tacos
directions: Place chili, beans and Ro-Tel tomatoes in a heavy boiler. Keep at a low heat, stirring often to keep from sticking.
Let simmer for a few minutes.
Cut up Velveeta cheese into the hot mixture and add the whipping cream, stirring constantly.
Low heat.
Let cheese completely melt, mixing well.
Serve over regular size Fritos.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Mix together dry ingredients in large bowl. Make a hole in center of dry ingredients. Add 4-5 eggs and milk. Mix together to make stiff dough. Let dry 10-15 minutes.

title: sallyann's supreme salsa
directions: Peel and mash garlic cloves with a morcajete or garlic press. Toast chilies on a hot griddle, peel off skin and put into blender with canned tomatoes, mashed garlic and 1/2 bunch rinsed cilantro. Coarsely chop on slow speed for 30 seconds.
Chop/dice tomatoes, green onions and rest of cilantro.
Mix together with chile mixture.
Add salt to taste.
Refrigerate.
Add or omit chilies for hotter or milder taste.

title: ham delights
directions: Cream margarine, poppy seed, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and chopped onion.
Completely slice through the middle of the rolls, separating the tops and bottoms.
Spread tops and bottoms of rolls with mixture.
Place ham and cheese on rolls.
Wrap in foil.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: peach cheese pie
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add eggs, sugar, milk and vanilla. Blend well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Drain and slice peaches, reserving 1 cup juice. Combine cornstarch and sugar.
Stir in reserved peach juice, lemon juice and almond extract.
Cook, stirring, until thick.
Arrange peaches, petal fashion, on cheese filling.
Garnish with maraschino cherries.
Spoon glaze over fruit.
Chill 1 hour.
If there is not enough peach juice to equal 1 cup, mash peaches to equal 1 cup.

title: meatless 3-step chili
directions: Cook rice in a 3-qt. saucepan as package directs with onion and celery added.
Five minutes before rice is done, stir in remaining ingredients except cheese.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in cheese and cook until melted.
Top each serving with shredded cheese.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients except eggs. Beat eggs and add last. Grease 9 x 13 pan with margarine. Bake in 325° oven approximately 40 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into casserole dish.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Place powdered sugar and peanut butter in bowl and mix until crumbly.
Set this mixture aside.
Mix instant pudding according to directions on the box.
Place crumb mixture into the cooled pie shell, saving a little of this mixture for the top.
Pour the pudding mixture on top of the crumb layer.
Sprinkle the top of this pie with the remaining crumbs.
If there is any pie left, keep it stored in the refrigerator.

title: chocolate crunch pie
directions: Prepare pudding with 1 cup milk according to package.
Fold in whipped topping.
Stir in 1 cup chocolate chips and cookies into pudding.
Spoon into pie crust.
Sprinkle with remaining cookies. Freeze until firm, 4 hours or overnight.
Let stand at room temperature for 10 minutes before serving.
Store leftovers in the freezer.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Grease a shallow baking dish and spread 1/2-inch thick with mashed potatoes.
Fill with beef and gravy and garnish top with mashed potatoes in large spoonfuls.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) about 20 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: mama's old-fashioned tea cookies
directions: Sift flour in biscuit bowl.
Make a "well" in flour.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and milk.
Pour all ingredients in flour "well" and mix like you would make biscuits. Roll dough (small amount at a time) on a floured board to 1/2-inch or thinner.
Cut with a cookie cutter dipped in flour.
Bake about 15 minutes in 350° to 375° oven or until golden brown.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: *Prepared as directed and cool.

title: batter for fish
directions: Mix all together and let set an hour.
If it seems too thick, add a little more water.
If too thin, add more flour.
Dip fish and fry in deep fat.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Grease 10-inch tube pan.
Combine apples, cinnamon and sugar; set aside.
In large bowl, combine remaining ingredients and blend thoroughly; batter will be heavy.
Spoon half of batter in pan and top with half of apples.
Repeat with remaining batter and apples. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 45 minutes, until top of cake is brown and firm to touch.
Remove from pan.

title: mock whipped frosting
directions: Mix together flour and milk and cook until thick. Let cool. Cream sugar, butter and vanilla. Add the cooked milk and beat with mixer until sugar is dissolved. Very good frosting for banana cake and your red velvet cakes or any cake.

title: mound bars
directions: Mix together and pat out in pan; let stand in refrigerator 24 hours.
Then cut in squares.
Dip in melted chocolate and wax.

title: tomato-basil soup
directions: Saut spinach in olive oil about 3 - 5 minutes. Add rest of ingredients & bring to simmer. If you can't find 28 oz. can crushed tomatoes, get diced and run through blender.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Use blender to mix first 8 ingredients. Then add, using a spoon to mix, the oatmeal and raisins. Mix all ingredients together and bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: not bad meat loaf
directions: Beat the eggs lightly in a large bowl.
Add everything else and mix well.
Put in loaf tin and bake at 350° for an hour.

title: bean supreme casserole
directions: Saute meat, onion and bell pepper; drain off fat. Add other ingredients, except cheese; simmer 10 minutes. Pour into large baking dish; bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Add cheese to top and bake another 15 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together in a mixing bowl real good. Add eggs, one at a time, and beat.
Add flour and beat.
Add sour cream, continuing to beat until well mixed.
Pour into
a greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
A cake with four layers can be made from this batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa.
Mix in cold milk, salt and vanilla.
Cook over medium heat until thickens.
Gravy is supposed to be on thin side.
Serve over hot biscuits.

title: quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pie shell and bake 1 hour at 350° or less.
Makes one deep-dish or 2 shallow pies.

title: russian tea
directions: Boil in 1 quart of water 3 sliced oranges, 2 sliced lemons, juice from 3 oranges, 1 lemon and allspice for about 10 minutes. Make tea (about 2 cups water and the 5 tea bags).
Add sugar to tea.
In a large pot, bring to a boil enough water to make 20 to 25 cups.
Add tea to hot water.
Strain fruit mixture into the large pot with the tea and water.
Add pineapple juice.
Heat, but do not boil.
When cool, put into containers and store in refrigerator.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Cook ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Drain juice off cans of beans.
Mix everything together and cook 30 to 45 minutes at 400°.

title: oven-easy beef stew
directions: Mix beef and vegetables in a 13 1/2 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Blend seasonings, Accent and tapioca.
Stir in tomato juice; pour over beef.
Cover tightly; bake in a 350° oven for 2 1/2 hours, or until meat is tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Break cake
in	small pieces and place in a large bowl. Mix sour
cream, milk, whipped topping and sugar until smooth. Fold into
cake.
Mix
sliced strawberries and glaze spread on top of cake mixture.
Chill several hours or overnight before serving.

title: spaghetti with chicken
directions: Cook chicken in enough liquid so that there can be at least 3 to 3 1/2 cups of liquid to cook spaghetti in and 1 cup of broth to use later.
Cook spaghetti; add soup, 1 cup of broth, salt and pepper to taste and rest of ingredients.
Bake in greased casserole dish in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: queen elizabeth's drop scones
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and about half the milk together.
Combine flour, baking soda and cream of tartar; add to mixture along with with rest of the milk and melted butter.
Add in raisins; blend well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto a greased baking pan and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Enough for 16 servings (1 per person).

title: mud pie
directions: Mix ground Oreo cookies with melted butter.
Press into bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie dish to form the crust.
Chill.
When chilled, add softened ice cream and freeze.

title: chicken and rice(heritage recipe)
directions: Place chicken pieces in slow cooker, sprinkle on rice.
Pour on soups mixed with water.
Cover and cook on low 6 to 8 hours.

title: butter
directions: Pour whipping cream into quart jar and close tightly.
Shake jar briskly for 25 to 30 minutes.
Pour through strainer, buttermilk will go through, butter will remain in strainer.
Enjoy!

title: homemade fresh apple cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well and add remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: "pineapple coconut pie"
directions: Beat eggs and add sugar. Mix well and add butter and beat until creamy. Add coconut and pineapple. Bake in unbaked pie shell at 350° until set.

title: italian zucchini crescent pie
directions: Cook and stir zucchini and onion in margarine for 10 minutes. Stir in parsley or parsley flakes, salt, pepper, garlic powder, basil and oregano. Combine eggs and Mozzarella cheese. Stir in zucchini mixture.

title: veal chops
directions: Flour the chops and brown in oil.
Drain oil and add the tomato sauce, garlic and oregano. Simmer about 30 minutes, then add 1 can black chopped olives 5 minutes before done.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: Place chicken and buttermilk in large shallow dish and marinate several hours.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Dip chicken pieces into flour mixture.
Fry in your favorite oil until crispy brown.

title: peanut butter crinkles
directions: In bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat first 6 ingredients until fluffy.
At low speed, beat in next 4 ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in sugar.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until browned.
Immediately press nuts or candies into cookies or press with thumb and fill with jam.
Cool.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 6 dozen.
(Very good just as they come out of the oven without candies or nuts.)

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Cook one minute after it comes to a boil.
Frost cake and continue to pull frosting up sides of cake until it begins to get firm.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a Bundt pan sprayed with Baker's Joy.

title: my grandmother's 2-layer cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, Crisco and sweet milk together real good. Add eggs and beat until mixed good.
Add vanilla flavoring.
Pour into 2 greased and floured cake pans.
Bake 25 minutes at 325°.

title: tomato fritters
directions: A colorful array of crisp, lightly steamed vegetables, this appetizing side dish can also serve as a hearty meatless meal for two.
The pungent, garlicky dressing is anything but bland. Sometimes I garnish with a little minced red bell pepper.
As soon as you top the dish with cheese, cover it with aluminum foil to trap the heat; this will help melt the cheese by the time you uncover the dish at the table.

title: grandma's shortcake
directions: Combine eggs, baking powder and salt.
Beat well.
Sift sugar; add gradually to egg mixture.
Fold in flour.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Serve with fresh strawberries on top.

title: plantation okra
directions: Cook bacon in a large skillet until crisp; remove bacon, reserving half of drippings in skillet.
Set bacon aside.
Saute okra and onion in drippings over medium heat 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes, green pepper and celery; cook 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add corn, salt and pepper; cook an additional 15 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Sprinkle with bacon.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda, powder and salt; set aside.
Mix together margarine and sugars, then add eggs and flour mixture. Add oatmeal and remaining ingredients.
Chill dough, then roll in balls and place on greased cookie sheet.
It's easier to handle if you keep dough chilled.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Layer 3 cups rhubarb, 1/2 package dry Jell-O, 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 package dry cake mix in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer again the same.
Pour 1 cup water over top.
Slice thin 1/4 stick margarine.
Lay on top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Yummy warm topped with ice cream.

title: sour cream enchiladas(serves 6)
directions: Save a few sliced olives for topping.
Mix sour cream, green onions, cumin, cheese, meat and olives and have ready.

title: fluffy white frosting
directions: Place all ingredients, except vanilla, in top of double boiler.
Beat over boiling water with a rotary beater until stiff. Take off heat and add vanilla.
Spread on cake.
Can be used on yellow layer with coconut, pineapple or strawberries.
Use with deviled food cake layers.

title: irish soda bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine the flour, salt, baking powder, baking soda, sugar and spices (if used). Add butter or margarine and cut in with a pastry blender or two knives until crumbly. Beat egg slightly and mix with buttermilk; add to dry ingredients and stir until blended.
Turn out on a floured board and knead until smooth (2 to 3 minutes).
Divide dough in half and shape each into a round loaf; place each loaf in an 8-inch cake or pie pan.
Press down until dough fills pans.
With a sharp knife, cut crosses on top of loaves about 1/2-inch deep in the middle.
Bake in a moderately hot oven at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves. The breads are delicious either warm from the oven or cold.

title: mile high pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into two graham cracker crusts.
Chill.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix sugars and cream with shortening.
Add peanut butter and eggs.
Mix well.
Blend dry ingredients.
You may have to mix with your hands.
Add vanilla.
Make into balls; press with floured fork.
Bake at 350° until barely brown around edges.
Let cool before removing from pan.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla. Mix lightly, but well.
Mix flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon in separate bowl.
Add flour mixture to first mixture and blend.
Add nuts.
Bake in two greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans at 325° for 1 hour or until it tests done.
Remove from pans at once and cool.
Makes excellent mini muffins!
Even something kids love!!

title: julie's favorite spaghetti
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef, onion and pepper.
Pour off excess grease.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, 1/2 cup water, a little black pepper, sugar and chili powder.
Cook about 2 hours. Cook spaghetti.
Drain off water and add sauce.
Sprinkle grated Parmesan cheese on top.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together and put into a casserole dish and cook until done.
Add one box of Lipton golden saute chicken and broccoli for a change.

title: fruit cake
directions: Melt butter in applesauce and cook.
Add other ingredients and last soda and flour.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Bake at 250°, when raised, turn heat to 275°.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Crush cookies and sprinkle in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. (Leave about 8 cookies for top.)
Melt butter and pour over cookies; mix.
Let stand in refrigerator for one hour.
Mix cream cheese, 1/2 container Cool Whip and powdered sugar until smooth. Spread over cookies and refrigerate another hour.
Make pudding and pour over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate another hour. Spread Cool Whip on top; sprinkle with leftover crushed cookies. Refrigerate or freeze at least 1 hour before serving.

title: my hero!
directions: Place the split roll on a plate. Open it so it will lay flat; spread with mayonnaise.
Place lettuce on roll.
Place the American cheese halves on lettuce with points extending outward. Roll up the beef slices and place on cheese.
Do the same with the ham and salami.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Garnish with pickle slices and olives.

title: squash casserole
directions: Place squash, milk and sliced butter in casserole dish. Sprinkle crackers over top add spray with spray butter.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes or until squash is tender and cracker crumbs are browned.

title: mom lippard's crisco pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl, mixing well.
Pour into greased angel food pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: make ahead potatoes
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Boil until softened.
Drain off water.
Add all other ingredients except margarine and paprika. Whip or mash until fluffy.
Add a small amount of milk if needed. Place in large casserole dish and refrigerate or freeze until ready to use.
Immediately before baking, drizzle melted margarine over top and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours. Makes 12 servings.

title: i don't bake bread bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9-inch loaf pan.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking soda and baking powder. Mix well.
Add yogurt and honey to flour mix and mix well.
Push globs of dough into prepared pan.
Level out to make nice shape. Bake 45 to 50 minutes.
This is a heart healthy low-fat bread. Each serving is 110 calories, 3.8 grams protein, 9 grams fat and 23 grams cholesterol.

title: date nut loaf
directions: Sift flour, sugar and baking powder.
Add and stir oleo and egg yolks; then nuts and dates.
Beat egg whites and fold into above mixture.
Bake for 1 hour at 325° in a tube pan.
Decorate top with candied cherries.

title: company beef casserole
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
Add onion, tomatoes, ketchup, grated peppers and parsley; simmer for 30 minutes.
Cook macaroni; drain and combine with meat mixture.
Season to taste.
Gently spoon mushroom soup from can into the mixture and mix lightly.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until top is bubbly and brown.

title: broccoli and beef bake
directions: Brown beef and onion and drain.
Add cream cheese, soup and stir until mixed and hot.
Place broccoli on a casserole dish and pour mixture over top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Unroll crescent rolls and lay over top of cheese and bake per directions on crescent roll can.

title: pickled eggs and red beets
directions: Wash beets; cut off leaves and stems, leaving about 1 inch of the root end.
Cook until tender; drain and skin.
Boil remaining ingredients together (except the eggs) for 10 minutes.
Let beets stand in this liquid several days.
Add whole cooked eggs to the liquid and refrigerate 2 days.

title: onion-glorified chops
directions: Clean and prepare ham for cooking.
Soak overnight in cold water.
Take out and wipe with paper towel.
Place ham in large cooker.
Put 6 colas over ham.
Fill cooker with water.
Place on top of stove and bring to a hard rapid boil.
Time for one hour after ham hits boiling.

title: mincemeat mini loaves
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease six 5 3/4 x 3 1/4-inch loaf pans.
In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
With pastry blender or 2 knives used scissor-fashion, cut in shortening until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
In small bowl, beat the eggs with the milk.
Mix the egg mixture, mincemeat, cranberries and walnuts into flour mixture.
Spoon in pans.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.

title: banana nut bread #2
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add egg to this mixture. Blend well.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed sugar, shortening and egg mixture.
Add 3 large mashed bananas. Add vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake in 350° oven for approximately 1 hour.
Insert toothpick in center; if it comes out clean, you're finished.
Wonderful eaten warm with a little butter.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and cream of tartar into a mixing bowl.
Add the shortening to the flour mixture and blend together until cornmeal-like consistency.
Pour milk into flour mixture slowly.
Add the egg and stir all together until a stiff dough.
Put on a lightly floured board and knead 5 times. Roll out to one-half inch thickness; cut with a floured biscuit cutter.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet for 10 to 15 minutes at 400°.

title: orange fruit cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream the shortening, first 1/2 cup white sugar and brown sugar. Add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Add flour and buttermilk alternately. Baking soda can be put in flour or buttermilk.
Grind raisins, nuts and orange rind.
Add to other ingredients.
Bake at 325°.
Check after 1 hour.
Dissolve remaining 1/2 cup sugar in juice of orange and pour over cake after it has been out of the oven for awhile.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix until crumbly the flour, brown sugar, cinnamon, oatmeal and melted butter.
Pat 1/2 of crumbs into greased 9-inch pan; cover with 4 cups rhubarb.
Combine sugar, cornstarch, water and vanilla.
Cook until clear.
Pour over rhubarb.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until rhubarb is tender.

title: homemade pancakes(hot cakes)
directions: Beat egg, add buttermilk.
Add all dry ingredients.
Add margarine, make sure skillet is hot before dropping batter.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine and pack firmly in loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.
Serves 8 people.

title: wild rice and sausage casserole
directions: Cook sausage until brown.
Add onion and celery and cook vegetables until clear.
Add 1 can cream of mushroom soup and stir. Add pimentos, mushrooms and rice.
Place in 3-quart greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: baked chicken casserole
directions: Sprinkle chicken with garlic powder, salt and pepper to taste.
Spread out in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Add slices of onion and green pepper. Cover with the soup. Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 325°.

title: green bean salad
directions: Slightly cook green beans.
Mix together all ingredients and serve.

title: chicken wings
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over chicken wings.
Marinate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(Can be kept warm in a crock-pot after cooking.)

title: banapple cake
directions: Place all ingredients, except nuts, in blender; blend well. Stir in nuts by hand.
Pour into Pam sprayed loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: tortilla roll-ups (3)
directions: Mix together and spread on tortillas, roll tortillas up tightly, put in covered container and refrigerate for 2-3 hours. Cut roll-ups into bite size pieces and serve.

title: slippery beef pot pie
directions: Boil roast in large pot with 2 quarts water.
Add salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste.
Cook 2 to 3 hours, until tender. Remove meat; shred it and place back into pot.
Add potatoes.
Mix flour and Crisco in bowl.
In another bowl, blend eggs and water. Stir half the egg mixture into the flour mixture, then add rest of egg mixture, a little at a time.

title: tater-topped casserole
directions: In a skillet, cook onion, celery and ground beef until meat is brown and vegetables are tender.
Drain.
Stir in salt and pepper. Spoon mixture into a greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spread soup over meat mixture.
Top with frozen potatoes.
Bake at 400° for about 40 minutes until bubbly.
Remove from oven and top with cheese.
Return to oven and bake until cheese melts, about 5 minutes.

title: easter salad(3 layer gelatin salad)
directions: Bottom Layer:
Drain liquid from pineapple and reserve. Prepare
gelatin
according
to package directions; color with green coloring.
Add
drained pineapple and put in 8 x 12-inch pan.
Chill until firm.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Add 2 soups and water.
Cook spaghetti and drain.
Add 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Pour meat mixture into spaghetti and cheese.
Mix in mushrooms and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: meat balls(finger food)
directions: Mix all together. Form into small balls. Bake on cookie sheet at 350° until brown (approximately 15 minutes) or brown in skillet on both sides.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and pat onto a cookie sheet.
Chill. Cut into squares and brown on each side.
Put in baking dish and add mushroom soup.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: to die for chocolate pudding cake
directions: Cook pudding per instructions on box.
Stir in cake mix.
Pour into well greased 8 1/2 x 11 x 2-inch cake pan.
Cover top of cake with chocolate pieces and nuts.
Pat into cake.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients in large bowl.
Stir in mayonnaise.
Gradually stir in water and vanilla until smooth and blended.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch round pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 30 minutes or until cake tests done. Cool and remove from pans. Ice with chocolate icing.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Beat 2 egg yolks until thickened.
Add lemon juice, condensed milk and 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Mix well and pour in pie shell.
Chill before serving.

title: light lemon meringue pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a heavy, 2-quart saucepan, combine 3/4 cup sugar, cornstarch and water.
Mix until cornstarch is thoroughly dissolved.
Add egg yolks and whisk thoroughly.
Bring to a boil over medium heat and allow to boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add margarine; mix well.
Add grated lemon rind and lemon juice and again mix well.
Allow the custard to cool.
Spoon the custard into the unbaked pie shell.

title: pinto bean cake
directions: Cook and mash beans while they are still warm.
Chop apples. Cream the margarine or Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add flour alternately with liquid from beans.
Add pecans, raisins, cinnamon, allspice, vanilla, chopped apples and mashed beans.
Pour into greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: okra casserole
directions: Saute onions and green pepper in butter.
Saute okra separately with salt and pepper.
When okra is tender, mix with onions and pepper.
Layer in casserole dish with fresh tomatoes. Slice olives and put on top.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: minted lima bean salad
directions: In medium size saucepan cook limas in 1 cup water with 2 sprigs mint.
Do not overcook.
Drain beans; rinse with cold water.
Place in a bowl and throw away the mint sprigs.
In a small bowl, whisk together mustard, vinegar, oil, salt, pepper and 2 teaspoons mint. Add this dressing and the ham to the beans. Toss and chill.
An hour before serving, bring to room temperature and toss with 1/2 head shredded Boston lettuce.
Garnish with fresh mint.
Double the amount for dressing mix and it will be tastier.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix 2 teaspoons pepper, oil, vinegar, salt and sugar.
Pour over vegetables.
Toss.
Store in refrigerator overnight.

title: sally lunn old-fashioned bread(favorite to serve with tea)
directions: Blend Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Mix dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Place in 9-inch square pan which has been rubbed with Crisco.
Bake in hot oven at 400° about 25 minutes. Makes 18 pieces, 3 x 1 1/2 inches.

title: beef-a-roni
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and pepper in greased skillet. Add tomatoes, catsup, salt and pepper. Cook 15-20 minutes. Cook macaroni in salted water until done; drain. Add macaroni to meat mixture in skillet. Simmer to blend flavors. Serves: 6-8.

title: sausage bread
directions: Thaw bread. Combine the 2 loaves and spread on a cookie sheet. Cook sausage with onion and drain. Spread in the middle of bread dough and top with green onions and cheese. Pull side of bread over, making a loaf. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Pour vegetables, soup, onion, mayonnaise and chestnuts in a casserole dish. Place in a 350° oven and bake 30 minutes. Remove from oven. Sprinkle with shredded cheese. Mix together crackers and margarine and sprinkle over vegetables. Bake 10 more minute or until top is brown.

title: crock-pot smothered steak
directions: Add cubed steak to crock-pot. Mix the other ingredients together and pour over the steak.

title: extra light rolls
directions: Boil and mash potatoes; add butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and sugar; cream together.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm milk.
Add to potato mixture.
Add flour until mixture is stiff enough to knead.
Knead well, about 10 to 12 strokes.
Place in greased bowl. Grease top of dough with butter.
Let stand in a warm place to rise.
Form into rolls and let rise again.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: easy red salad
directions: Combine gelatin and boiling water; stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Add cold water and let partly congeal.
Fold in other ingredients and pour into large mold or individual molds.
Makes 16 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon and ground cloves.
In a large bowl, beat sugar, oil and eggs.
Add and beat in pumpkin.
Add dry ingredients in 3 additions alternating with water or milk and vanilla.
Fold in nuts and raisins or dates.
Pour batter in a greased pan and bake for about an hour.

title: chewy oatmeal fruit bars
directions: Mix oats, flour and apple juice in a large bowl until lumps are gone.
Stir in cinnamon and raisins.
Mix vanilla in the warm water and add, mixing well.
Stir in banana and optional dried fruit.
Let stand 15 or 20 minutes.
Mix again and pour into nonstick 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 325° or 350° for 1 hour or until browned.
Makes 16 servings.
Calories 131, fat 1 gram.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Heat together celery soup and milk.
Add Cheddar cheese. Combine cooked noodles, tuna, mayo, celery, onion, green pepper and pimento.
Add this to soup and cheese mixture.
Pour into casserole dish.
Preheat oven and bake at 400° for about 15 to 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Do not overbake.
Serve with extra cheese on top.

title: southern corn pudding(microwave dish)
directions: In 1 1/2-quart glass casserole, melt butter with High power for 30 to 45 seconds.
Add corn, eggs, salt, pepper, sugar, onion and milk.
Mix well.
Bake with High power for 15 to 20 minutes. Stir halfway through baking time.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt in greased 8 or 9-inch square baking pan.
Make 2 holes in the dry ingredients. Pour oil into one, the vinegar and vanilla into the other.
Pour the milk over all and mix until well blended and smooth.
Bake at 350° until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean (about 30 minutes).
Cool in pan on wire rack.
Spread with Chocolate Glaze.

title: tuna mousse
directions: Crumble cheese into soup and heat until cheese melts.
Blend well.
Soften gelatin in water, then stir into soup mixture.
Set aside to cool.
Flake tuna into bowl and mix in vegetables, nuts and salt.
Stir Miracle Whip and sour cream into soup mixture. Blend well, then fold into tuna mixture.
Chill well.
This makes a good mold.

title: chunky chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, mix together cake mix and chocolate pudding.
In large bowl of mixer, blend eggs, sour cream, water and oil until smooth.
Pour liquid ingredients into dry and blend until ingredients are well combined and smooth. Stir in floured chips and pour into well-greased 10-inch angel food or Bundt pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes until toothpick or knife inserted in center comes out clean of batter. (The chips will be melted throughout the cake.)
Allow to cool for 20 minutes in pan, then remove.
Frost with chocolate frosting or whipped cream.
This cake is very rich and can serve a large crowd.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg yolks. Add soda gradually. Add dry ingredients to flour, then add gradually to egg mixture. Add raisins, nuts and beaten egg whites. Pour into cake pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except sugar); roll into small balls.
Roll balls in confectioners sugar.
Do not flatten.
Place on cookie sheet (not greased).
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut tops off peppers.
Remove seeds and membranes from inside peppers.
Mix all ingredients together. Fill peppers with stuffing and cover with foil.
Bake for 35-45 minutes.

title: grapefruit salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Split grapefruit lengthwise from stem to naval and remove all membrane and seeds, saving meat and juice.
Should measure 2 cups; if not, add some juice.
Stir into Jell-O mix.
Fill empty hulls with mixture and chill in refrigerator.
When firm, split shells and serve on lettuce with small amount of mayonnaise if desired.

title: lemon lust
directions: Mix
magarine, flour and nuts.
Press mixture into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Blend cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread mixture over cooled crust.
Blend together pudding and milk until smooth.
Spread over cheese filling and top with additional whipped topping.
Sprinkle with more crushed nuts.
(Also very good substituting lemon pudding with butter pecan, pistachio or your own favorite flavor.)

title: oriental chicken pitas
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
Combine vinegar, soy sauce and sesame oil.
Pour over chicken mixture and toss gently.
Line pita halves with lettuce.
Spoon 1 cup chicken mixture into each pita half.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together the shortening and sugar.
Add the mashed bananas and eggs, mixing well after eggs.
Add the flour, soda, salt and chopped nuts.
Let stand in a greased loaf tin for 20 minutes.
Bake at 350°
for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: cork 'n cleavers spinach rice salad
directions: After cooking rice, refrigerate a few hours to cool completely. Add vinaigrette, soy sauce and sugar; mix well.
Add spinach, celery and green onion; toss all together.
Sprinkle with crumbled bacon before serving.
Serves 4.

title: special k roast
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients, then add Special K.
Pat mixture into an 8 x 8-inch greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until golden brown on top.

title: russian tea (velvet brown)
directions: Boil lemon rind with cloves and water 5 minutes. Add sugar and tea. Stir in lemon and orange juice.
Serve hot. Serve 16 cups.

title: nacho pie
directions: Brown meat and onions until done, drain. Stir in tomato sauce and taco seasoning, bring to a boil, reduce heat, simmer for 5 minutes.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Mix and chill. Roll dough in balls.
Roll balls in powdered sugar.
Place 2-inches apart on greased baking sheet. Bake 12 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken, then skin, debone and cut into pieces.
Put into baking dish.
Mix broth with both soups and pour over chicken. Season with salt and pepper.
Mix flour and buttermilk with melted margarine. Pour over chicken mixture and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until brown.

title: jogger's punch
directions: Put ingredients into a blender and blend until well mixed. Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: spicy grilled pork tenderloin
directions: Combine soy sauce, sugar, cumin, mustard, paprika, garlic and cilantro in plastic food storage bag.
Fold under thin ends of tenderloin to make an even thickness; tie ends with kitchen string.
Add tenderloin to bag. Push out all air; seal. Refrigerate and let marinate for 30 to 60 minutes.
Prepare grill or preheat broiler.
Oil grill or broiler-pan rack.

title: *coleslaw
directions: Combine vegetable oil, vinegar, sugar and salt.
Bring mixture to a rapid boil.
Slowly pour hot mixture over cabbage,
green pepper and onion; do not stir.
Let set 1 hour.
Refrigerate.

title: german gingerbread
directions: Cream sugar, flour and butter until crumbly; set aside 1 cup. Mix soda and spices into mixture.
Add eggs and milk.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with reserved mix.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 30 minutes.
Serve with Lemon Sauce.

title: chocolate pizza candy
directions: Melt chocolate flavored coating and chocolate chips in a heavy saucepan over hot water.
When melted, take from heat.
Add marshmallows, peanuts and Rice Krispies.
Mix until well coated. Spread in a greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Sprinkle with M&M's.
Melt vanilla flavored candy coating and vegetable oil over low heat, stirring constantly.
Drizzle over pizza.
Let cool.

title: sonny's salsa dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight to allow flavors to blend.
Serve with Tostitos brand 100% white corn restaurant style tortilla chips.

title: mom's chocolate pie
directions: Combine in a double boiler sugar, flour, salt, milk and cocoa; boil 10 minutes.
Add egg yolks and cook until mixture is thick. Remove from heat and add vanilla and margarine.
Let cool and pour in pie shells.
Spread meringue lightly on the pies or chill 2 hours and top with Cool Whip.
Makes 2 pies.

title: loaded fried potatoes
directions: Fry potatoes and drain well. Place potatoes in bottom of 9 x 13 baker dish. Crumble bacon up on top. Sprinkle cheese on top of bacon. Place in a 350° oven until cheese is melted. Top with sour cream before serving.

title: stir-fry chicken and broccoli
directions: Stir-fry chicken in hot oil in large skillet until browned. Add broccoli and other vegetables.
Stir-fry until crisp-tender. Mix broth, soy sauce, cornstarch, sugar, garlic powder and ginger; add to skillet.
Bring to boil; boil one minute.
Prepare rice. Serve chicken and vegetables over rice.

title: cowan cream puffs
directions: Combine margarine with water and bring to a boil.
Take off the heat and add flour.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Take batter, using a teaspoon, and drop on an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake in a 400° oven for 30 minutes, slightly golden brown.

title: hoisin-chili marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Marinate pork or boned chicken breasts 2 to 3 hours.
Baste with sauce while grilling.

title: dutch baby(breakfast)
directions: Place butter in large heatproof dish (a quiche pan works well) and put in 425° oven to melt.
Mix eggs, milk, flour and salt until smooth.
Pour batter into hot dish.
Toss apples in lemon juice and arrange pieces over batter.
Sprinkle brown sugar over top.
Bake in 425° oven for 20 minutes.
It will puff up, then collapse in center while browning.

title: crabmeat au gratin
directions: Saute onions in butter; add cheese and then milk.
Bring to a boil and add crabmeat (seasoned to taste).
Serve with crackers.

title: fried potatoes, okra and pepper
directions: Slice potatoes, okra and hot pepper.
Sprinkle salt and corn meal over the vegetables.
Fry until golden crunchy brown.

title: swedish fruit balls
directions: Melt oleo, add dates.
Cream eggs and sugar.
Add to oleo mixture in frypan.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Cool. Add other ingredients.
Form into small balls and roll in coconut. Store in refrigerator in tin.
Will keep a month.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix
pineapple
and pudding, including pineapple juice. Add marshmallows
to
the above.
Fold in Cool Whip and nuts. Refrigerate overnight or serve in 3 to 4 hours.

title: smothered steak
directions: Cut steak into serving pieces.
Pepper to taste and roll in flour.
Sear on both sides in hot fry pan with just enough shortening to prevent sticking.
Remove and place in covered roaster or deep pan.
Pour soup and water over meat and simmer at 275° for 45 minutes in oven.

title: western casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain. Mix together all other ingredients. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: ruby frost punch
directions: Combine cranberry and lemon juices with sugar until sugar dissolves.
Chill.
To serve, pour over ice in punch bowl; add ginger ale and slightly softened sherbet.
Garnish with lemon slices.
Makes 24 punch cup servings.

title: german chocolate icing
directions: Mix sugar, milk, butter and egg
yolks in saucepan.
Cook 10 minutes, stirring constantly. Add coconut, vanilla and nuts. Allow to cool. Spread on cake.

title: blueberry bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line a 12-cup muffin pan with paper liners or spray with cooking spray.
In a small bowl, add skim milk to bran.
Let soak for 5 minutes.
In a large bowl, mix flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
In a separate bowl, blend oil, apple juice, applesauce, molasses, sugar and bran mixture.
Mix well. Add egg and egg white.
Mix well.
Fold in dusted blueberries. Add applesauce mixture to flour mixture.
Mix until moistened.
Fill muffin cup 3/4 full. Bake 20 to 25 minutes. Remove from oven and cool 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.
Per serving contains 160 calories and 3.0 g fat.

title: mom's pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and Crisco with a fork until crumbly.
Add ice water, one tablespoon at a time, until dough forms a ball.
Roll out on a floured surface.
The less the crust is handled, the more tender and flaky the crust will be.

title: cranberry gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; let cool slightly.
Beat cranberry sauce and sour cream together until smooth and the gelatin.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish and chill overnight.
Easy to make and very delicious.

title: dirt cake
directions: You'll need 1 flowerpot (plastic is best) and 1 bunch of silk flowers.

title: cocoa pebbles goodies
directions: Melt butter and peanut butter in saucepan, stirring frequently.
Add marshmallows and cereal.
Stir until marshmallows start to melt and stick to cereal.
Remove from heat.
Press mixture firmly into buttered 8-inch square pan.
Chill 1 hour. Cut into squares.
Store in cool place.
Makes 16 squares.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown onion,
pepper
and ground beef. Drain. Season to taste with
salt	and pepper.
Add celery soup and milk. Stir. Cook macaroni and drain.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: In a large bowl, mix 1 cup flour, sugar, lemon peel, salt and dry yeast.
Combine milk and oleo in saucepan.
Heat over low heat until milk is warm (120° to 130°).
Oleo does not need to melt. Add to the dry ingredients.
Beat for 2 minutes at medium speed of mixer.
Add egg and 1/3 cup flour.
Beat at high speed for 2 minutes. Stir in enough flour (about 1 2/3 cups) to make a soft dough.
Turn out onto floured board.
Knead dough about 5 to 10 minutes.
Cover and let rest for 20 minutes.

title: homemade chicken vegetable egg drop soup
directions: Prepare soup as directed on the package. Drain the canned vegetables and add to the soup. Add the can of chicken with the broth it is in. Bring to a boil. Lower the heat. Slowly pour the beaten eggs into the soup while beating the soup with a wire whisk. Cook for 1 minute. Serve in bowls with noodles, soy sauce and mustard.

title: cheese balls or logs
directions: Mix well.
Roll into balls or logs and chill.
Roll in chopped nuts and garnish with cherries or olives.

title: cornpatch cornsticks
directions: Set oven at 425°.
Melt butter in oven in cornstick pan or shallow muffin tin.
Mix meal, flour, baking powder, soda and salt together.
Mix corn and egg; stir in cornmeal mixture until just mixed.
Stir in hot butter and pour into sizzling pan.
Bake about 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes about 10 ears or muffins.

title: freezer pops
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Add 2 cups cold water and pour into molds and freeze.
Makes 20 pops.

title: contest carrot cake
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and oil. Into mixture blend flour, soda, buttermilk and cinnamon.
Stir in chopped pecans, grated carrots and lemon extract, mixing well.
Bake in a tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
When cool, cover with glaze.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Add half of dressing.
Stir until all is dampened.
Pat down.

title: lentil dip
directions: In a medium sized pan, fry onion and garlic in oil until brown.
Add water, lentils and the remaining ingredients except cheese and picante sauce.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 to 20 minutes, until the lentils are fully cooked, adding more water if the mixture is too thick.

title: shrimp with butter sauce
directions: Boil all ingredients, except the shrimp, for 20 minutes.
Add the shrimp and cook until done.

title: husbands delight
directions: Brown hamburger. Drain. Combine tomato sauce, garlic salt, and pepper with hamburger and simmer. In a bowl, combine sour cream and cream cheese.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Arrange cooked broccoli in 9 x 13-inch pan or large flat casserole.
Cut chicken in large bite-size pieces; place over broccoli.
Mix together soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and sherry; pour over broccoli and chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese, then bread crumbs and drizzle the melted butter over the top.
Bake, covered, at 350° about 1 hour until bubbly and very hot.
Serves 8.

title: bean sprout hot dish
directions: Mix all together and bake for an hour and a half.
I usually bake it at 375° to 400°.

title: melt in your mouth scones
directions: Warm buttermilk to lukewarm.
Add yeast; dissolve.
Add remaining ingredients.
Dough should be soft.
Let rise.
Make into desired shapes.
Fry in hot oil.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix sugar, butter, flour, soda and tartar together.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Then add vanilla and nuts.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pistachio pudding mix as directed on box.
Add crushed pineapple, drained.
Add Cool Whip.
Add marshmallows.
Add pecans; toss lightly.
Store in refrigerator.

title: chicken oregano
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Arrange, skin side up, in one layer in a 3-quart baking dish (13 1/2 x 8 3/4 x 1 3/4-inch).
Stir together the lemon juice, olive oil, garlic and oregano; spoon over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, in a preheated 400° oven for 30 minutes.
Remove breast portions (they should be tender) and keep warm.
Continue baking remaining chicken until it is golden and tender, 15 minutes longer.
Serve chicken and thin sauce with freshly cooked hot spaghetti.

title: sausage biscuits
directions: Flatten each biscuit.
Spread with sausage and add grated cheese.
Roll up and cut in half.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze.
When frozen, store in plastic bags.
Take out as many as you need at a time.
Bake on greased sheet until done at 350°.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients; stir in cheese.
Cover, refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Makes 3 cups.
Keeps well in refrigerator for 2 to 3 weeks.
May add more sugar and garlic powder to taste.

title: sausage and macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Fry sausage, onion and green pepper until lightly brown.
Stir in flour and salt.
Add milk.
Cook over low heat until thickened.
Stir constantly.
Place alternate layers of macaroni and sausage in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Pour balance of sauce over all.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 400° for approximately 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: tea
directions: Put enough water to cover the tea bags in a small pan.
Let come to a boil.
Add tea bags; turn to simmer for 5 minutes.
Add the sugar until blended.
Add enough cold water to make 1/2 gallon tea.
Refrigerate.

title: vegetable gumbo
directions: Melt bacon drippings in 10-inch skillet. Saute onion until soft. Add okra. Cover. Steam over low heat for 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Steam, covered, for 5 to 10 minutes. Do not stir.

title: cranberry fluff
directions: Chop one package washed cranberries and add sugar and marshmallows.
Refrigerate overnight, covered.
Add chopped apple with peeling.
Whip carton of whipping cream and mix well all ingredients.
Keep covered in refrigerator.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine flour, sugar, soda, salt and cinnamon in large bowl. Make well in center.
Stir together remaining ingredients.
Add to dry ingredients and stir until smooth.
Spoon into two greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Mix together sugar, Carnation milk and butter.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Pour over marshmallow cream and chocolate bits.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and nuts.

title: strawberry punch bowl cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients by hand.
Take 1 large Merita angel food cake and break it into bite-size pieces and add to the mixture.
Put into a bowl and hold.
Wash and cut into quarters about 1 quart strawberries and mix in 2 bags of strawberry gel. Pour on top of cake mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Heat cider vinegar, oil and sugar until sugar melts.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour on vegetables.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Drain and serve on lettuce leaves.

title: one dish chicken & stuffing bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix water and butter.
Add stuffing and mix lightly.
In a 3 qt. shallow baking dish spoon stuffing along the center.
Arrange chicken on each side of the stuffing and sprinkle with paprika.
Mix soup, milk and parsley.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and bake in the preheated oven for 30 minutes or until done.

title: super stuffing
directions: Fry sausage, onion and celery until sausage becomes brown and onion tender. Add the rest of ingredients; drizzle broth and toss lightly until evenly mixed. Bake at 375° in covered 4 quart casserole until hot (45 min.) or bake covered alongside bird for last 30 min. of roasting. Makes 12 cups.

title: corn fritters
directions: Beat egg and add remaining ingredients.
Beat well.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot fat and cook until golden brown.

title: grammie jardine's baked beans
directions: Wash beans and pick over.
Soak overnight in cold water; drain in the morning.
Cover with water; boil until the skins peel back when you blow on them (about 20 minutes or so).
Save the water. Put beans in pot; add all the ingredients, except bacon or salt pork.
Top with bacon or salt pork; cover the pot.
Bake at 300° for about 5 to 6 hours, or until done (check beans every 1/2 hour or so and add more water if necessary).

title: cabbage stew
directions: Brown ground beef (drain).
Add cabbage and onions.
Sprinkle chili powder onto mixture.
Add enough water to cover cabbage and onions.
Boil until cabbage turns colors.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and pinto beans.
Turn down heat and simmer.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Optional:
You may use 1 pound ground deer meat instead of ground beef.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Core and chop the cabbage.
Place in boiling water for a few minutes.
Drain.
Mix together meat, rice, egg, onion, carrot and salt.
Mix together sugar, tomatoes and chives.
In a casserole dish, layer cabbage-meat mixture and tomatoes.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 350° or can be cooked in a crock-pot on low 8 hours.

title: apple yorkshire
directions: In ovenproof skillet, heat butter.
Add apples and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Saute until glazed and soft.
Beat eggs, flour, salt and milk together in large bowl.
Fold in apples. Turn into skillet or a baking dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 425° until puffy and firm.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Serve warm.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Add next three ingredients. Chill dough at least one hour.
Roll dough into balls the size of walnuts.
Roll in a mixture of 2 teaspoons cinnamon and two tablespoons sugar.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: old fashioned no cook ice cream(makes 1 gallon)
directions: Beat eggs with electric mixer until they are light in color. Add sugar to eggs; beat at high speed until mixture is thick.
Add vanilla, salt and evaporated milk.
Continue beating until sugar is dissolved.
Mix thoroughly into the whole milk.
Freeze, following manufacturer's instructions.
Very good.

title: hot dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except nuts.
Place in baking dish. Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Serve with your favorite crackers: Wheatables, Ritz, etc.

title: chicken nachos
directions: In saucepan mix soup, salsa and chicken.
Over low heat, heat through, stirring occasionally.
Serve over chips, top with onions and olives.
Serves six.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops. Trim the fat. Put pork chops on bottom of pan. Place a layer of sliced potatoes, layer of onions, layer of potatoes and layer of onions. Pour mushroom soup and water (already mixed) over casserole. Cover and bake in oven at 400° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken italiano
directions: Brown fillets in olive oil until just cooked through.
Add remaining ingredients, except parsley, and stir to blend.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, in covered skillet for 20 to 30 minutes. Top with parsley, Parmesan cheese and Mozzarella cheese and allow to melt.
Serve over hot, cooked egg noodles.
Serves 4.

title: spaghetti and meat sauce
directions: Cook hamburger until brown, drain grease.
Add olive oil, onion, tomato sauce and tomato paste, oregano and basil.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours or two.
Cook spaghetti according to directions on package and serve with garlic bread and salad.

title: milk freeze
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Beat at low speed to blend.
Beat at high speed until mixture stands in peaks.
Freeze for 3 hours until firm as ice cream.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cake batter.
This will cover the cake dough.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: trev.-snack
directions: Mix well all the ingredients with melted butter, stirring constantly.
Cook in large roaster for 45 minutes at 250°.

title: chicken lasagna
directions: Prepare lasagna according to package directions; drain.
In medium saucepan, combine soups, milk, onion, dill, bouillon, seasoned salt and pepper.
Heat through, stirring constantly. Blend in sour cream.
Remove from heat.

title: pineapple chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a large shallow baking pan, melt margarine with oil in the oven.
Remove pan.
Combine flour, salt, paprika and pepper in a plastic bag.
Piece by piece, coat chicken by shaking it in the bag with the seasoned flour.
Arrange floured chicken in baking pan in one layer.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes. Turn chicken.
Combine pineapple, green pepper, green onions, brown sugar and sherry; pour over chicken.
Lower heat to 375°; bake until chicken is golden brown and sauce is thick (45 minutes).
Serves 8.
Enjoy.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut
broccoli, onion, apple and celery together.
Leave in refrigerator
overnight.
Mix
in another bowl mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.
Mix together when ready to serve.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken and mayonnaise.
Add all other ingredients, stirring gently to avoid breaking up chicken.
Cover and place in refrigerator at least 4 to 6 hours, preferably overnight.
Will keep well (without grapes) 2 to 3 days.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Whip butter 15 minutes. Add sugar, vanilla, flour and potato chips. Mix well and drop from teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: nut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add water and remaining ingredients (except egg whites), adding
nuts last.
Add beaten egg whites.
Beat a total of 4 minutes.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix avocados with lemon juice and salt.
Layer all ingredients (except cheese).
Cover with cheese.
Refrigerate.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: baked fettucine
directions: Preheat the oven to moderate 350°.
Add the fettucine to a large pan of rapidly boiling water and cook until just tender. Drain well and set aside.
While the pasta is cooking, melt the butter in a large pan.
Add the chopped onion and stir constantly over low heat until the onion is tender.
Add the drained fettuccine to the pan.

title: chess pie
directions: Beat eggs real well.
Add sugar and beat until thick.
Add other ingredients and stir.
Pour into unbaked crust and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sticky buns
directions: Grease a 12-cup Bundt pan with 1 tablespoon butter.
Sprinkle nuts in bottom of pan.
Drop marmalade by spoonfuls around bottom of pan.
Mix together the brown sugar and cinnamon in a separate small bowl.
Melt margarine in a separate small bowl.
Now take the separated biscuits and dip each one in the margarine and then roll it in the sugar mixture to coat it.
Stand biscuits on edge in pan in wagon wheel spoke fashion.
