Drizzle any remaining margarine over top and sprinkle any remaining sugar mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool 5 minutes and then turn upside down on serving plate.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Enjoy!

title: black-eyed pea dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese, in food processor or blender.
Place in 1-quart casserole dish and top with cheese. Bake in a 350° oven or on stove top for approximately 20 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and pull off of bones.
Mix cream of mushroom soup with cream of chicken soup and add one can of water to soup mixture.
Put chicken in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan or casserole dish.
Pour soup mixture over chicken.
Mix stuffing mix with 2 cups of hot water.
Spread stuffing over top of chicken and soup and bake in a 350° preheated oven, for 30 minutes or until stuffing is golden brown.
Makes 8 servings.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Saute mushrooms, over medium heat, for 2 to 3 minutes.
Put mushrooms in a bowl.
Add all other mixed ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Drain well before serving.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Blend in egg.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to mixture.
Add vanilla. Divide dough into two parts.
Chill 1 to 2 hours, so dough will be easy to handle.
Roll dough, one part at a time, to 1/8 inch thickness and cut with cookie cutters.
Keep other part refrigerated until ready to roll.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: ham casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except chips.
Place in buttered casserole and top with chips.
Bake until bubbly.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
May be prepared ahead of time.

title: coffee punch
directions: Add chocolate milk or water if too strong. It can always be weakened and is better to have rich coffee taste.

title: graham cracker squares
directions: Place a layer of graham cracker squares in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Over medium heat, place margarine, milk, sugar and egg (beat before adding to other ingredients).
Cook this, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil; remove from heat.
Add coconut, nuts and crumbled graham crackers; mix well. Pour over squares.

title: corn mcchshu
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in butter in large skillet.
Add corn and Ro-Tel tomatoes and heat.

title: papaya chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, curry powder, salt and pepper and coat chicken.
Brown coated chicken in oil in a skillet on high heat.
Drain and arrange in a shallow baking dish in a single layer.
Bake for 40 minutes or until tender.
Pour off oil from skillet.
Dissolve cornstarch in 3 tablespoons papaya nectar and set aside.
Pour remaining nectar in skillet.
Add the ginger and sugar.
Simmer on medium heat scraping up any bottom pieces. Stir in cornstarch and cook until thickened.
Stir in lemon juice. Drain fat from baked chicken.
Arrange papaya slices over chicken and cover with sauce.
Return to oven and cook 5 minutes more. Serve with steamed rice.

title: teriyaki tidbits
directions: In large saucepan, over medium heat, combine preserves, barbecue sauce and teriyaki sauce.
Heat until hot and bubbly, stirring constantly.
Stir in wieners, pineapple and green pepper. Heat thoroughly.
Transfer mixture to chafing dish, keeping warm over low heat.
Serve with toothpicks.
Makes 16 servings.

title: mincemeat surprised cookies
directions: I made this
first
It was and is our special Christmas cookie.

title: jellied cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello in the hot water.
Mix plain gelatin in cold water and sugar.
Let stand.
Chop the cranberries, oranges, apples. Add the pecans and pineapple and juice from oranges.
Mix all together and let jell.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: spinach dip
directions: Strain spinach and mix all ingredients.
It is best to make this the night before.
Cut bread into chunks.
Enjoy!!

title: hot fruit salad
directions: Mix sugar, salt and flour.
Add egg and juice.
Cook until thick.
Stir to keep from sticking.
Cool and serve on cold fruit or serve as a warm salad.
You may add 7 or 8 marshmallows and allow to melt if desired.
I added canned fruit cocktail (drained) to the sauce and served as a warm salad.
Any fruit may be used.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare broccoli according to package directions.
Cook broccoli until crisp-done.
Mix mushroom soup with 1/3 cup milk. Add to cooked rice.
Add 1/4 pound grated cheese to the rice soup mixture.
Stir in the drained broccoli.

title: christmas scent
directions: Combine. Add additional water as needed. May be stored in the refrigerator several days and reused. Yield: 4 cups.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all listed ingredients together in a pan.
Layer on top with a package of slivered almonds.
Then top with 1 cup of grated Cheddar cheese.
Top with 1 cup broken Cheez-Its.
Pour 1/2 stick melted margarine on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Very good.

title: maw maw's cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 10 minutes.

title: easy refrigerator roll dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large mixing bowl.
Stir in sugar, shortening, egg, salt and 3 cups of flour.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Place dough in greased bowl; turn greased side up.
Cover loosely with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours, or until ready to use.
(Dough can keep up to 4 days in refrigerator at 45° or below.
Keep covered.)

title: rice with mushrooms and peas(riso con i funghi e piselli)
directions: In medium saucepan melt
butter
and
saute onion until tender.
Add rice and mushrooms;
cook
until half of the rice is nicely browned.
Pour in chicken broth and water.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Lower
heat
and
simmer for 15 minutes. Add drained peas and cook an additional 5 to 7 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.
Serve immediately.
This is wonderful served with grilled meats or skewered beef, lamb or shrimp.

title: best chocolate icing
directions: Mix sugar, chocolate, milk and oleo. Boil 3 minutes (no more). Remove from heat and add syrup and vanilla.
Beat until thick enough to spread on layers.

title: donatella
directions: Combine all the ingredients and place in large baking dish or casserole and bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes until hot and bubbly.
Tastes better leftover.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In Ziploc bag, crush potato chips. Beat egg and milk together.
Cut up chicken into finger food size. Dip chicken pieces in milk mixture. Toss in Ziploc bag with potato chips and shake. Place chicken pieces on baking sheets. Bake 10 minutes on each side.

title: chicken divan
directions: Place broccoli and chicken in a greased dish.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: date bars
directions: Beat eggs well; add sugar and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to egg mixture; add dates and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chewy brownies
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan.
Add cocoa, sugar, vanilla and beaten eggs.
Blend well and add flour and nuts.
Mix well and spread in a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: corn flake treats
directions: Bring karo and sugar to a boil and take off of heat. Add peanut butter, vanilla, and cornflakes. Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: sardine spread
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender or food processor using enough mayonnaise or salad dressing to moisten to spreading consistency.
Serve on party rye.

title: jello roll-ups
directions: Mix gelatin and water in a 1 1/2 to 2-quart bowl.
Microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir to dissolve.
Add marshmallows to gelatin mixture.
Microwave 1 minute or until marshmallows are almost melted.
Stir until smooth.
Pour into a 8 or 9-inch square pan, lightly sprayed.
Refrigerate 45 minutes.
Loosen edges with knife.
Start at 1 end, roll up tightly like jelly roll.
With seam down, cut into slices and refrigerate.

title: dried apple stack cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add molasses, mixing well.
Add eggs; combine dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture, alternately with buttermilk, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Place dough on floured surface (work in enough flour to make dough easy to handle).
Divide into 9 balls.
Press each ball of dough evenly over bottom of a lightly greased 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until light brown.
Cool slightly.
Remove from pan; cover each layer with apple filling, until all 9 layers are used.

title: apricot-coconut balls
directions: Combine apricots and coconut.
Add sweetened condensed milk and blend well.
(I use my hands.)
Shape into small balls.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Let stand until firm, about 3 hours.
After firm, may roll once again in confectioners sugar.
Yield:
4 dozen candies, depending on size you make.
May be stored, uncovered, at room temperature, from 3 to 4 days.

title: miracle rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; set aside.

title: shaum torte
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add salt and cream of tartar. Continue beating until stiff (20 to 30 minutes).
Sift sugar and add slowly while mixing.
Add vinegar and vanilla.
Beat well. Pour into buttered spring-form pan.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix ingredients in order given.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking for 45 minutes.

title: ham chowder
directions: In a soup kettle, cook carrots, celery, onion and potatoes in water until tender, about 20 minutes.
Cook ham, butter, salt and pepper, then add to veggies.
Blend flour in milk until smooth. Add to soup, stirring constantly until mixture boils.
Turn heat to low and simmer partly covered.

title: tamale meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown beef, onions and garlic in a large frying pan.
Drain off any fat.
Add tomatoes and chilies and corn, and bring to a boil.
Remove from the heat and stir in corn meal, oregano, milk, cayenne pepper, eggs and salt.
Mix well and pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake 45 minutes or until firm.
Let rest 10 minutes before slicing.
Serve with salsa on the side.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: white potato pie
directions: Cream mashed instant potatoes, then combine eggs, salt, milk and melted butter or margarine.
Mix well; pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 or 40 minutes until filling is firm.
(Yields 6 servings.)

title: mandarin cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, eggs and mandarin oranges with juice with electric mixer.
Divide into three 9-inch greased and floured layer pans. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Cool completely.
Mix instant pudding, Cool Whip and pineapple with juice with electric mixer.
Spread between layers and on top and sides.
Keep covered in refrigerator.
Better if made the night before.

title: red velvet pound cake
directions: Mix and bake in a large, greased and floured tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together and drop by teaspoon full on cookie sheet. Bake at 350 degrees for 5 to 10 minutes. Cookies will be soft when they come out of oven. Enjoy!

title: homemade zucchini cookies
directions: In a large bowl, combine together butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and stir in zucchini.
Add baking powder, spices and flour.
Mix well and then add two of the following 3 ingredients:
either raisins, chocolate chips or the chopped walnuts.
I prefer 1 cup of the chocolate chips and 1 cup of the raisins.
Bake approximately 10 minutes or until cookies are firm to touch and the edges are brown at 375°.

title: west virginia cornbread salad
directions: Crumble cornbread and mix with all remaining ingredients.

title: cock-a-leekie soup
directions: Place chicken, bacon, chopped bones, herbs and most of the leeks into a large saucepan and cover with water.
Put the lid on and let it simmer for 2 or 3 hours, topping up with more water if necessary, until the bird is cooked.
Season to taste, then strain, picking out the chicken and cutting it into serving pieces and spooning out the marrow bones.
Add these to the soup, together with the stoned prunes and the remaining chopped leeks. Simmer gently for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: old fashioned potato candy
directions: In bowl mix potatoes, vanilla and confectioners sugar.
Mix until stiff.
If not stiff enough add more sugar until stiff.
Use a cutting board.
Sprinkle confectioners sugar on board.
Roll out.
Spread peanut butter on thin or thick.
Roll up and cut.

title: meatballs in lemon sauce with mashed potatoes
directions: Beat eggs slightly in large bowl; add beef, crumbs, salt and pepper, lemon rind and 1 tablespoon lemon juice.
Combine gently; form into 24 balls.
Heat 3 cups of water with beef broth in Dutch oven; add meatballs.
Lower heat; poach gently 15 minutes, turning once.
Cook pared potatoes in salted water until tender.
Drain and reserve liquid.
Mash potatoes with margarine and milk (use some reserved liquid to make creamier).
Stir flour with water to make a smooth liquid.
Remove meatballs to heated platter; skim off any fat.
Add flour mixture slowly to broth, stirring until thick.
Stir in 1 tablespoon lemon juice; simmer 5 minutes.
Cook peas, drain and arrange on platter with meat and potatoes.
Spoon sauce over meat and pass remaining sauce. Sprinkle with parsley.

title: apple pie filling
directions: Mix all except apples well in a saucepan.
Cook until thick and bubbly.
Pour over the apples in the jars and seal.
Process in a water bath for 20 minutes for quarts.
(Can mix the apples with the cooked mixture and then put in jars and process.)

title: holiday seafood spread
directions: Combine cream cheese and dressing.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Chill.
Serve with crackers or vegetables.
Makes 2 cups.

title: pimento cheese sandwich spread
directions: Grate cheese on coarse grater, then grate hot hard-boiled eggs over cheese. Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Will keep well in refrigerator for several weeks.

title: breakfast casserole(feeds a bunch!)
directions: Place the bread in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread cheese over the bread.
Place the meat on top.
Beat the eggs, salt, mustard and milk together.
Pour over the bread, cheese and meat.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour.
(Do not preheat oven.)

title: chewy walnut squares
directions: Stir together egg, brown sugar and vanilla. Quickly stir in flour, baking soda and salt.
Add walnuts. Grease an 8-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Cookies will be soft in the middle. Leave in pan until cool.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix; roll into walnut size balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Drain well.

title: pudding cookies
directions: Mix well and form into small balls.
Flatten with hand on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: christmas jelly candy
directions: In 1 1/2-quart saucepan combine gelatin and sugar.
Add fruit juice; wait 5 minutes.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cook and stir until gelatin dissolves.
Add lemon juice.
Pour into shallow pans or paper baking cups.
Cool.
Chill until firm.
(If desired, loosen sides.)
Carefully turn out of pans, using a wide spatula. Cut with cookie cutters.
Place on wire rack to dry.
Cover pans or store cutouts in single layers, between waxed paper, in airtight containers up to 5 days.
Make 24 (1 1/2-inch) pieces.

title: chocolate clusters
directions: Melt chocolate pieces, butter and marshmallows in large saucepan over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Mix in vanilla, oats and coconut thoroughly.
Drop mixture onto waxed paper. Chill until firm.
Makes approximately 3 1/2 dozen.

title: fruit slush
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir until sugar is dissolved. Freeze overnight.
Let stand out about one hour and chop into small chunks.
Spoon into glasses.
Add 7-Up or diet soda to each glass.
Stays well in freezer for at least a week.

title: apricot salad
directions: Mix crushed pineapple and sugar in saucepan.
Bring to a full boil.
Add Jell-O to dissolve.
Add cream cheese.
Remove from heat and stir until cream cheese is completely blended.
Add ice water to thicken.
Let cool and then add chopped nuts and celery. Set in refrigerator until mixture starts to jell.
Prepare Dream Whip according to package directions.
Fold into Jell-O mixture. Chill 24 hours in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Blend oil, sugar and eggs, then add remainder of ingredients. Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Pour into pans and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Let cool for 10 minutes before removing from pans. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: fruit ice cream soda
directions: Thaw frozen fruit or slice banana.
Puree in blender.
Force puree through a sieve to remove berry seeds.
Put 1/4 cup puree in a tall glass.
Add milk and vanilla ice cream or matching fruit ice cream.
Almost fill with chilled soda water.

title: turkey or chicken casserole
directions: Combine all together.
Put into casserole.
Sprinkle some of the grated cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Freezes well.

title: elderberry jam
directions: Combine berries, sugar and vinegar in a large pot.
Bring slowly to a boil, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Cook rapidly until thick, stirring frequently.
Pour into hot jars, leaving 1/4-inch headroom; seal.
Process in boiling water bath for 15 minutes.
Makes about 3 pints.

title: pie crust
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in lard. Add vinegar and cold water to beaten egg.
Add to rest of ingredients.
Form 4 balls.
No matter how this dough is rolled or handled, it will still be a flaky dough.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix chopped nuts and coconut together.
Spread in bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake mix as directed on package. Pour over nuts and coconut. Do not spread; just let it spread itself.
Combine rest of ingredients and drop by teaspoon on batter, using all the filling.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes. As it cools, top will indent to look like an "earthquake."

title: barbecued burgers
directions: Saute the onion.
Add the ground beef, salt and corned beef. Cook until meats are brown.
Add the barbecue sauce.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Then serve on bun.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and bananas. Sift together dry ingredients.
Stir into banana mixture.
Add cold water and vanilla.
Mix well and turn into greased or sprayed loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: most requested men's dip
directions: Serve with chips and crackers.

title: baked beans
directions: Put beans in casserole dish.
Add catsup, mustard, onion and brown sugar.
Mix thoroughly.
Place bacon slices on top of beans. Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes or until bacon is crisp.

title: macaroni and meat salad
directions: Combine ingredients and chill.

title: charleston chili
directions: Brown meat and onions. Pour off fat. Add celery, peppers, crushed tomatoes, tomato paste and water. Cook 1/2 hour. Add Chili-O, oregano, basil, Worcestershire sauce and beans. Cook at low temperature 1 hour, stirring frequently. Add more water as needed. Add cayenne pepper sauce, chili powder and salt to taste.

title: marinated slaw
directions: Mix vegetables together and set aside. Bring remaining ingredients to a boil and pour over cabbage mixture. Stir well and let stand 12 hours in refrigerator. Stir before each use. Keeps well.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into cookie sheet or jelly roll pan that has been sprinkled with chopped nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn on towel; roll up.
Cool, unroll and fill with filling.

title: cottage cheese pie
directions: Mix well and pour in unbaked pie shell. Sprinkle with cinnamon or nutmeg.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: banana split cake
directions: In
a
x 13-inch pan, prepare a graham cracker crust (using crumbs, sugar and butter).
Bake and cool crust.

title: chocolate chip cupcakes
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt in mixer bowl. Stir water, oil, vinegar and vanilla into dry ingredients until mixture is smooth.
Fill paper-lined cupcake tins half full (about 1/4 cup).
Put 1 teaspoon of filling into center of each cupcake. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Do not need to be frosted.
Makes about 3 dozen cupcakes.

title: fudge sauce for hot fudge cake
directions: Boil about 5 minutes with a continuous stir so not to stick to pan.
This is good over
a butter recipe cake or devil's food cake mix.

title: smothered pork chops
directions: Cube your pork chops. Season with Tony's seasoning. Cook until almost done. Then put your onion in and saute. Put into bowl and make your gravy in juice and oil left from your meat. When the gravy is ready, put your meat and onion back in gravy and smother for about 30 minutes. Put over rice or potatoes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: rice-stuffed goose
directions: For stuffing, melt butter in large skillet.
Add rice, onion and celery.
Cook slowly, stirring constantly, until rice is lightly browned.
Add water, bouillon cubes, parsley and seasonings.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until rice is tender (add more water if rice begins to stick).
Set aside to cool.

title: creamy cheesy potato soup
directions: Cover potatoes, celery and onion with water.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and cook until potatoes are tender.
Reduce heat to low and add soup, cheese, milk, margarine and ham.
Simmer until cheese has melted, stirring occasionally.

title: easy zucchini relish
directions: Combine zucchini, sugar, water, vinegar and horseradish in a saucepan. Bring to a boil. Boil 5 minutes, stirring often. Remove from heat. Add gelatin and stir until dissolved. Ladle quickly into hot sterilized small jars or frozen containers. Cover tightly; cool. Store in freezer or refrigerator up to 2 weeks. Makes 3 cups.

title: european veal meatballs
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in mixing bowl and mix well. Shape mixture into 1 1/2 inch balls.
Brown in hot oil 5 to 6 minutes in a large skillet.
Remove meatballs, reserving pan drippings.
Stir and add flour to drippings; blend.
Reduce heat; add mushrooms, sour cream and browning and seasoning sauce, stirring constantly.
Gradually stir in milk.
Return meatballs to skillet and cook over low heat 10 minutes.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: beef salad
directions: Place all in a large bowl and pour dressing over all.
Stir well.
Enjoy.

title: corn on the cob with seasoned dipping sauce
directions: Cover corn with cold water in large bowl and soak overnight. Prepare barbecue (low heat).
Grill corn until cooked, approximately 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, melt butter in heavy medium saucepan over low heat.
Add green onions, garlic, salt, thyme and bay leaf and stir for 5 minutes.
Add wine and lemon juice and cook 2 minutes.
Transfer sauce to bowl.
Serves 4.

title: raisin drop cookies
directions: Add water to the raisins and boil for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Stir in soda and let stand.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add vanilla and beaten eggs and the cooled raisins with their liquid and flour sifted with the baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Stir in nuts and drop by teaspoon on greased sheet.
Leave plenty of space between cookies.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
Store in jar.

title: grilled salmon
directions: Prepare charcoal fire.
Cut 2 pounds of salmon fillets into 6 pieces of equal thickness.
Slice 2 red onions about 3/8-inch thick crosswise.
Mix 1/4 cup light olive oil with 2 tablespoons olive oil.
Salt and pepper the onion slices, brush with oil mixture and put on grill in a place where heat is low.
Grill onions for 5 minutes.
Turn; grill for 5 minutes.
Salt and pepper salmon fillets.
Brush them with oil mixture.
Put them on grill over medium-hot fire; grill for 3 minutes.
Turn; grill for 3 minutes, until firm and springy when pressed with finger.
Serve salmon and onions.

title: arabian rice
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter.
Add rice and pine nuts. Fry, stirring constantly, until rice and nuts are golden, about 5 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to boiling. Reduce heat and simmer, covered, about 20 to 25 minutes.
If too moist, uncover for last 5 minutes of cooking.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Place in container first the lettuce, onion, bacon and cauliflower.
Mix sugar and mayo together.
Put over the other ingredients.
Add cheese, pepper and salt.
Let set 8 to 10 hours before serving.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Press down with a fork.
Bake at 425° until golden brown.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs, flour and soda with buttermilk.
Add vanilla, chopped nuts and coconut. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add blueberries and pineapple.
Let mixture set partially (chill).
Add Dream Whip or Cool Whip.
Let set until jelled.

title: berry pink cloud
directions: Prepare the dessert topping mix according to package directions.
Tint pale pink with few drops red food coloring. Fold in strawberries and pineapple; chill.
Stir before serving. (Add a little milk if the mixture is too thick.)
Trim with strawberries.
Makes 8 servings.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Butter a 2-quart casserole.
Prepare rice according to package directions, cooking 5 minutes less than time recommended.
Cook peas in boiling water in a covered saucepan, only until separated.
Drain.
Put peas on bottom of casserole. Layer turkey on top.
Spread rice evenly over turkey.
Combine soup and milk.
Pour evenly over rice.
Do not mix.
Sprinkle paprika generously on top.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes or until browned and bubbly.

title: lemon butter
directions: Let water come to a boil.
Mix sugar and cornstarch together with lemon juice.
Add eggs slightly beaten and butter.
Mix all ingredients together in boiling water.
Stir constantly until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove and put into a bowl.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and onion 5 minutes; drain.
Combine soup and cream.
Stir in carrots and fold in squash and onion.
Mix melted butter with dressing and spread 1/2 in pan.
Layer with squash mixture until all is used.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Soak for 4 hours in salt water.

title: easy corn muffins
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease bottoms only of 12 medium muffin cups or line with paper baking cups.
Combine corn meal, flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Stir in milk, egg and vegetable oil.
Mix until just moistened.
Stir in corn and red pepper. Fill muffin cups about 3/4 full.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes. Immediately remove from pan.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: barbecued beef strips
directions: Slice steak 1/8-inch thick while partially frozen.
Brown in hot oil; stir frequently.
Add tomato sauce, mustard, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce, water and sliced onion.
Cover and simmer for up to an hour, at least 30 minutes.
For a tangier barbecue sauce, stir in a little red wine vinegar or cider vinegar to taste before pouring over rice or noodles.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix 3/4 cups sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon in large mixing bowl.
Cut biscuits into fourths and roll into balls.
Roll the biscuit balls in the sugar/cinnamon mixture.
Alternate chopped pecans and biscuit balls in a well-greased (butter) Bundt pan.
Mix 1 cup sugar, 1 tablespoon cinnamon and 3/4 cup melted butter.
Pour over biscuit balls and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Let it stay in the pan for 5 minutes before removing from pan.

title: shortcut clam chowder
directions: In medium saucepan cook bacon until crisp.
Drain, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Cook onions in reserved drippings until tender.
Add potato soup, milk and undrained clams.
Simmer uncovered 5 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add bacon and garnish with paprika.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Brown onion in oil.
Drain tomatoes and add pulp, reserving juice.
Brown well; add tomato sauce, juice, celery and green pepper.
Add 2 cups hot water and shrimp.
Simmer until thickened. Add salt substitute, pepper, parsley and onion tops.
Serve over hot, fluffy rice.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chili-mac
directions: Brown meat and onion in shortening.
Mix with all other ingredients and bake for 35 mins. at 350 degrees.

title: corn casserole
directions: Blend together the cream cheese, butter and eggs.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° in a 3-quart casserole.

title: luscious lemon bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Oil bottom of 8-inch square pan lightly. For crust, combine oil, sugar and salt in large bowl. Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Add flour and milk.
Stir with spoon until well mixed and crumbly.
Spoon into pan.
Press evenly onto bottom.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine thawed potatoes (be sure they are thawed well), sour cream, onion, soup and cheese.
Spoon into a large, buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle buttered corn flake crumbs on top of each.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Yields 12 to 16 servings.
This dish freezes well.

title: veggie bars
directions: Spread crescent rolls flat on ungreased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes; cool.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Beat all ingredients with a mixer at medium speed.
Bake this mixture in 3 greased layer pans at 350° for 30 minutes until done.

title: chili(yield: 8 servings)
directions: 1. Brown meat, onions and garlic in large heavy pot.

title: sweet cucumber pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers 24 hours in the lime solution.
Wash out lime water, then soak 1 hour each for 4 times.
Bring sugar, spices and vinegar to a rolling boil.
Pour over cucumbers and let sit for 12 hours.
Bring to a boil and cook 1 hour or until clear.
Pack (with liquid) cucumber pickles into hot jars and seal.

title: scrumptious rhubarb custard pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and nutmeg.
Beat this into the eggs. Stir in rhubarb.
Put this in a pie shell.
Dot this with butter or margarine, then add a lattice top crust.
Bake at 400° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Check and put foil around the edge of crust if it gets too dark.
Cool before serving.
Yum!

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat slowly; drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally, to keep from scorching on bottom.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: cherry salad
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in only half the amount of water on the directions on package.
Then add pie filling, pineapple and nuts.
Let stay in refrigerator until firm.

title: hot fruit casserole
directions: Drain fruits.
Cut pineapple and peaches in half.
Arrange fruit in layers in a large, deep casserole dish.
In top of a double boiler, cook other ingredients until smooth and thickened. Pour over fruit.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, heat until bubbly hot.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: sweet potato casserole for microwave
directions: Peel and cook the potatoes; peel the apples, if desired. Slice the cooked potatoes 1/3 to 1/2-inch thick and thinly slice the apples.
Toss together in a 2-quart casserole.
In glass measure, microwave the butter (melt) and add enough maple syrup to make 1/3 cup.
Add cinnamon and salt.
Pour over potatoes and apples.
Microwave, covered, until the apples are tender, 5 to 6 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: beef steak
directions: *Try other steak cuts for variation.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream together shortening and 1 cup sugar in bowl. Beat until light and fluffy. Blend in egg and molasses. Add dry ingredients. Blend well. Shape dough into 1 1/4-inch balls. Roll in sugar. Place balls about 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 12 minutes; makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: crazy cake
directions: Mix up and pour 2 cups lukewarm water over that and mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Bake sweet potatoes until done.
Peel back top and scoop out inside of potato.
Whip potato with 2 to 3 tablespoons margarine. Mix in brown sugar, cinnamon, pineapple, flour and marshmallows. Put mixture into baking dish and bake, uncovered, at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: chocolate dipped apricots
directions: Line a cookie sheet with waxed paper. Melt chocolate chips in a small saucepan over low heat or in microwave on High, stirring every 30 seconds, until smooth.
Remove saucepan from heat.
Dip apricots into chocolate to partially coat.
Refrigerate on lined cookie sheet 20 minutes, or until chocolate sets.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and chop chicken breasts.
Add soup, mushrooms and pimentos.
Pour into 2 1/2 or 3-quart ungreased casserole.
Top with stuffing.
Pour broth over all.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until nicely browned.

title: coconut bar candy
directions: Pour milk over sugar.
Boil rapidly for 12 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cool.
Beat in coconut and flavorings.

title: honey cake(meduolis)
directions: Beat honey, gradually adding sugar and cream.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Sift flour and soda.
Add flour, spices and butter gradually to honey mixture, beating constantly.
(For a richer color, add 3 tablespoons burnt sugar.)
Pour batter (about 1-inch thick) into baking pan which was greased and floured.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: strawberry twinkie cake
directions: Place Twinkies in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spoon crushed pineapple over Twinkies, then add bananas, then pudding as directed on box.
Then layer on top of bananas.
Then layer Cool Whip on top of vanilla pudding.
Sprinkle top with chopped nuts and then place cherries around top.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix Crisco, vanilla, sugars, and water; beat until fluffy. Add eggs.
Add soda and salt to flour; add this mixture to the rest.
Stir in semi-sweet morsels.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 9 minutes.
Makes 120 cookies.

title: broccoli cheese muffins
directions: Mix and bake in greased muffin tins at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Melt Velveeta cheese and margarine in microwave.
Add powdered sugar, cocoa and vanilla.
Stir until well blended.
Pour into pan, refrigerate and cut into squares.

title: angie hickson's christmas cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add well beaten eggs and milk.
Stir in dry ingredients, then add nuts and fruit to dry ingredients. Add batter to brandy or whiskey to moisten.
Drop on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and cottage cheese (softened).
Spread in pizza pan.	Pour bottle of taco sauce over and smooth over. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese
over.
Cut
green	pepper	and tomato fine; add next.
Cut
black
olives
into
slices and sprinkle over (takes about 1/2 can).
Then
chop
lettuce fine and top. Cover well and refrigerate at
least
hours.
Dip
up
with Tostitos chips.

title: rice pudding
directions: Boil skim milk and rice for one hour, then add beaten eggs, sugar, vanilla and half and half.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Add raisins if desired.

title: brown sugar fudge
directions: Melt 1 cup sugar and Carnation canned milk.
Stir until sugar melts again.
Add 2 cups of sugar slowly.
Bring to a boil.
Stir constantly until forms soft ball stage.
Add vanilla and beat until cool.
Add nuts.
Stir and put into pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: freezer cole slaw
directions: Toss together cabbage, pepper, onion, carrots and salt and let stand 1 hour.
Combine in medium saucepan sugar, vinegar, celery seed and mustard seed.
Boil 1 minute.
Cool until lukewarm.
Pour over cabbage mixture and stir until all ingredients are combined.
Freeze until ready to serve.
Thaw 45 minutes before serving.
Store in covered dish.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix well and add 3 well beaten eggs.

title: curried beef and onions
directions: Melt margarine and add curry.
Fry the beef until brown.
Add water to almost cover and simmer.
Add the onions and carrot.
Add garlic powder and salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until beef is tender and serve with rice or mashed potatoes.

title: swedish nut cake
directions: Mix by hand in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: arroz con gandoles
directions: In a large pot, put the oil.
When oil is
hot, put 1 tablespoon of sofrito, 4 tablespoons tomato sauce, 2 packages of sazon, 1 package of sazon con achiote, 1/2 teaspoon garlic, pepper and salt.
Simmer until brown, then add 6 cups of water; bring to boil.

title: black walnut coconut bars
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar and add flour.
Mix well and pour in a greased 9 x 9 inch pan and bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.

title: wild rice bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.

Use a warm bowl and mix the 2 1/2 cups water, yeast mixture, brown sugar, molasses, butter, salt, Potato Buds and 2 cups flour. Beat until smooth. Add wild rice and enough flour to make a soft dough. Turn out on a floured board and knead for 10 minutes.
Place dough in greased bowl and let rise until doubled or 2 hours. Divide into 4 parts. Form into loaves and place in well-greased pans. Bake 30 to 35 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool on wire rack.
This is especially good with cheese whip and olives.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Cut into 1
x 2-inch squares.

title: green bean and corn casserole
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a medium bowl; stir well. Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 8-inch square baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients in a small bowl.
Toss gently. Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.
Sprinkle with shredded Swiss cheese and return to oven for 5 more minutes.

title: grandma's famous lasagna(yield:  8-10 servings)
directions: 1. Brown meat with garlic powder.

title: play dough
directions: Combine all ingredients in pan.
Cook low to medium heat, stirring constantly, until ball forms.
Remove from heat.
Put on wax paper and knead until cool.
Can color all one color while cooking or can divide into 3 parts and color each part and then knead.
Lasts a long time if kept in a plastic Ziploc bag when not in use.

title: calico beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut bacon into bite-size pieces.
In large skillet, cook bacon until done; drain.
Add ground beef and onion to pan; brown thoroughly.
Add ketchup, brown sugar and vinegar.
Mix well.
Empty beans into 3-quart casserole (drain liquid from butter and kidney beans).
Mix and add cooked beef mixture.
Bake, uncovered, for 35 to 40 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: beef supreme
directions: Mix together in a bowl, hamburg, tomato sauce sprinkled with onion flakes, salt and pepper.
Set aside.
In another bowl mix cheese, sour cream, milk and green pepper.
Set aside.

title: cheese log
directions: Mix and roll in chili powder.

title: english cookies
directions: Cream together brown sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, coffee, soda, baking powder, flour, raisins and nuts, cinnamon and nutmeg. Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until done, 7 to 10 minutes (depends on oven).
These are soft cookies.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice and add egg to juice.
Stir in vinegar.
Combine sugar and flour and add to egg mixture.
Cook over medium heat.
Stir until thickened.
Cool.
Stir dressing into apples; fold in pineapple, Cool Whip and 3/4 cup peanuts. Garnish with remaining nuts before serving.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine vegetables and salt.
Cover with ice and mix thoroughly.
Let stand 3 hours; drain well.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour over the vegetables.
Bring to a good boil only.
Seal at once in hot sterilized jars.
Makes 8 quarts.
Chill before serving.

title: troy's turtle cake
directions: Melt package of caramels with 1/2 cup sweetened condensed milk.
Stir cake mix with margarine and 1/2 cup sweetened condensed milk.
Spread less than 1/2 of batter in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 6 minutes at 350°; remove from oven. Sprinkle with nuts.
Spread melted caramels on top.
Sprinkle chocolate chips.
To other half of batter, add 3 tablespoons water and spread on top of chocolate chips.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes (no longer) at 350°; remove from oven.
Let cool and serve.

title: tabouli(makes 8 to 12 servings)
directions: Place bulgur wheat in large bowl or stainless steel pan. Combine boiling water and salt and pour over bulgur wheat. Allow to set for 45 to 60 minutes until bulgur is tender. Add lemon juice, olive oil and garlic and mix thoroughly. Put mixture in refrigerator overnight.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, coconut and powdered sugar.
Melt butter and add to mixture.
Add peanut butter.
Form into balls. In double boiler, melt chocolate chips and paraffin.
Dip balls in mixture, then put on waxed paper until cooled.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Place bread cubes in casserole or a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over bread.
Bake 1 hour in a 325° oven.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg, then flour and baking powder alternately with milk.
Fold in blueberries.
Bake in greased or paper lined muffin pan at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Mix dry ingredients; cut in shortening.
Add milk and let dough set for 20 minutes.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thick and cut into squares.
Fry in oil.
Serve with honey, cinnamon/sugar or powdered sugar.

title: keebler salad
directions: Mix buttermilk and instant pudding, mixing well. Add mandarin oranges. Fold in Cool Whip and crumbled cookies.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: be-deviled butternut squash
directions: Cook and mash squash.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Bake in casserole 20 minutes at 400°.

title: scripture cake
directions: Grease and flour a 10 x 4-inch angel food cake tube pan. Preheat oven to 325°.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and allspice onto waxed paper.
Cream butter, brown sugar and honey.
Add eggs, beating with an electric mixer, until they are light and fluffy, about 3 minutes.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup of the flour mixture over the fruits and nuts.
Add remaining flour mixture alternately with the milk to the fluffy butter mixture. Beat until smooth.
Stir in fruits and nuts.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Mix zucchini and salt in a colander and let drain for 15 minutes.
Combine with other ingredients and mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls into 1/2-inch hot oil.
Brown on both sides and serve hot.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except crackers.
Spread crackers on top.
Cook for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Mix and cook all ingredients for 20 minutes.
Put in jars while hot.
Makes 12 pints.

title: holiday truffles
directions: Melt chips over low heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in flavoring and chocolate frosting.
Refrigerate until firm (1 to 2 hours).
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Mixture will be sticky.
Roll balls in shredded coconut.
Store in refrigerator.
Ground nuts or cocoa may be used in place of coconut.

title: date bars
directions: Pit dates and cut into quarters.
Mix together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add dates and nuts to flour mixture. Beat eggs.
Add melted butter and combine mixtures.
Bake in 8 x 12-inch pan for 30 minutes in moderate (350°) oven.
When slightly cool, cut into bars.
Roll each bar in powdered sugar.

title: scalloped potatoes with cheese
directions: Cook uncovered 1 hour at 350°.
Break cheese up and mix in. Stir a few times while cooking.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Put noodles in hot water to soften (no need to precook).
If tomatoes are whole, cut into small pieces.
Saute onion, pepper and garlic in nonstick pan sprayed with no-fat cooking spray.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, drained mushrooms, spices and sugar.
Cook approximately 2 to 3 minutes.
Defrost spinach; drain well between paper towels.
Mix cheeses, eggs and spinach in a bowl.

title: granny's chocolate gravy
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then add milk and place on stove top at medium to high heat.
Bring to a boil and simmer until thick.
Stir continuously to avoid sticking.
Add butter and serve over hot biscuits.

title: chocolate covered coconut balls
directions: In a medium bowl beat softened butter and powdered sugar together until well mixed, add milk and mix.
Stir in the coconut. Mix well.
Roll into 1-inch balls and refrigerate until set. Melt chocolate and shortening over a double boiler, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat when melted and stir to make sure the shortening is fully incorporated.
Use toothpicks to hold the balls while dipping in the chocolate.
Set on wax paper to dry.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a greased 8-inch square pan at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and shrimp jambalaya
directions: In a Dutch oven, heat oil over medium heat until hot, but not smoking.
Add sausage; saute 5 minutes until brown.
Remove to a large bowl.
Add chicken in batches to oil and saute 1 minute for each batch or until golden brown.
Add to sausage.	Add onions, bell pepper, 3/4 of the scallions, 2 tablespoon parsley, garlic, and bay leaves to pot.
Add tomatoes and the juice along with the remaining seasonings.
Cook, stirring 3 minutes, breaking up tomatoes with wooden spoon. Return sausage and chicken to pot. Stir in rice and broth.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer without stirring for 30 minutes or until rice is tender and moist, not soupy.
Remove from heat; stir in shrimp; cover and let stand 10 minutes.

title: teriyaki potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes; scrub thoroughly with a vegetable brush.
Cut tiny new potatoes into quarters or medium potatoes into 1-inch pieces.
Place potatoes in a 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe casserole. Add margarine or butter, teriyaki sauce, garlic salt, Italian seasoning, black pepper and red pepper.
Toss to combine.
Cover; microcook on High for 12 to 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender, stirring twice during cooking.
Stir before serving.

title: spinach enchilada casserole
directions: In skillet, brown first 4 ingredients.
Add the next 8 ingredients to the skillet; cover and simmer approximately 10 minutes.
Cut tortillas into quarters and dip into melted butter. Cover bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan with half of tortillas. Spoon half of beef mixture over tortillas.
Sprinkle with cheese, 1 1/2 cups.
Arrange rest of tortillas.
Spread with sour cream. Then rest of beef mixture.
Sprinkle rest of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato-bean soup
directions: In a large saucepan, cook and stir celery, carrots and garlic in hot margarine over medium heat for 4 minutes or until tender. Carefully stir in broth, potatoes and dill.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, for 20 to 25 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
With the back of a spoon, lightly mash about half of the potatoes in the broth.
Add the drained beans to the potato mixture.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in greased baking dish.
Combine dry ingredients and work in melted butter.
Sprinkle over apples and bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: homemade macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni as per instructions on box.
Drain and place over low heat.
Add milk, butter, cheese, salt and pepper.
Stir until melted.
Pour into casserole dish.
Arrange thin slices of cheese on top and brown in oven.

title: beef orientale
directions: Cut meat in 1-inch pieces.
Place in a skillet and brown quickly.
Drain pineapple and add enough water to make 2 1/4 cups. Stir liquid, vinegar, soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce, sugar and salt into meat.
Mix cornstarch and water; stir in mixture.
Cook until thick.
Stir in pineapple, peppers, tomato chunks and onion. Cook until glazed, about 10 minutes.
Serve over rice or chow mein noodles.

title: blender popovers
directions: In an electric blender, whirl together all the ingredients, scraping down once or twice until smooth.
Pour into muffin tin that has been heated at 450° for a few minutes.

title: cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese.
Add and beat in sugar.
Add egg yolks, salt and flour; blend in milk and vanilla.
Beat egg whites; fold into mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then at 375° for 15 minutes, then at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Boil peas for 2 minutes. Drain and let cool.
Mix mayonnaise and sugar together.
Set aside.
In a large clear bowl, layer lettuce (torn into bite size pieces), onion, peas, green pepper and cheese.
Lightly press cheese down. Carefully spread mayonnaise mix evenly over cheese.
Sprinkle with bacon bits. Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut margarine into pieces; place in bottom of casserole. Place chicken breasts next. Mix water and soup. Place cheese slices on top of breasts. Spoon liquid on top of breasts and cheese. Place 2 cups of stuffing on very top. Bake in 325° oven (uncovered) for 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together except ginger ale.
Add it at serving time.
Yields:
50 servings.

title: roasted venison steak
directions: Line casserole dish or large deep dishpan with foil.
Chop steaks into bite-size pieces.
Place steak pieces in pan and cover with ketchup.
Chop onion and bell pepper and spread over steak. Stir together.
Put remaining ketchup on top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° until meat is done.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: fried salt pork
directions: Slice pork.
Add to water and let stand for awhile or overnight.
Drain well.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Dredge in flour. Fry slowly in a greased skillet until golden brown.
Serve with biscuits.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix peanut butter, butter and powdered sugar.
Roll into balls.
Chill or freeze.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Bring stock or water to a boil in large soup kettle.
Add vegetables, tomato soup and seasoning.
Reduce heat and simmer until vegetables are tender.
Serve with crackers.
Serves 6.

title: wheat rolls
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients well; use rotary beater.
Stir in flour.
Cover with damp cloth; let rise until double.
Punch down; let rise again.
Divide into rolls.
Let rise until double.
Bake 25 minutes at 400°.

title: macaroni salad with ham and cheese
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well; chill.
Serve on a platter lined with greens.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients in a large bowl and refrigerate.

title: citrus wild rice
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer until tender, 40 to 50 minutes.
Check after 30 minutes to see that rice is not sticking to pan; if it is, add a little water.
Serve with Hawaiian Chicken Kabobs.
Makes 3 cups.

title: coconut candy
directions: Mix first five ingredients together and shape into balls.
Mix together chocolate and wax in double boiler.
Dip balls into chocolate.
Place on wax paper.

title: green bean and corn casserole
directions: Bake 1 hour at 350° or microwave 20 to 30 minutes.

title: maple syrup barbecue sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Place ribs in pan.
Rub with garlic, pepper and salt. Pour 1 cup barbecue sauce over ribs.
Turn to coat.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Then broil 6 inches from heat, turning until caramelized, about 5 minutes.

title: zippy chili dip
directions: Fry and drain ground beef.
Stir in beans, salsa and chili powder.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Sprinkle with green pepper.
Serve warm with chips or vegetable sticks.
Makes about 3 cups of dip.

title: harvey wallbanger cake
directions: Mix all together and bake in Bundt or angel food cake pan for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit trifle
directions: In medium bowl, toss fresh fruit with sugar and liqueur (or juice).
Let stand at room temperature, tossing occasionally, about 30 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt
stick	of
butter
and mix with graham cracker crumbs.
Press
into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix eggs, 10x sugar
and softened butter for 20 minutes. Drain pineapple and add to the mix.
Pour into pan; cut bananas on top of mixture. Spread Cool Whip
and put nuts and cherries on top.
Refrigerate until set.

title: spicy banana pecan cake
directions: In a large bowl, cream together sugar, oleo and oil until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Stir together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and cloves. Combine banana and milk; add to cream mixture alternately with flour mixture, beating until smooth after each addition.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Turn batter into greased and floured tube pan. Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Invert on wire rack and cool. Dust with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: batter fried chicken
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; mix well.
Dip chicken pieces into batter.
Heat 1-inch of oil in a large skillet to 375°; add chicken and brown quickly on all sides.
Reduce heat; cover and fry 25 minutes or until chicken is tender and golden brown, turning occasionally.
Drain well on paper towels.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: meal-in-one mexican salad
directions: Cook ground beef until brown.
Add chopped onion; cook until tender.
Stir in beans, French dressing, water and chili powder. Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: anadama bread
directions: Stir cornmeal into boiling water in a large bowl, adding the cornmeal very slowly.
When mixed, add shortening, molasses and salt.
Cool.
When lukewarm, add 1 package yeast dissolved in 1/2 cup warm water.
Add the flour, enough to make a stiff dough. Knead well and put in warm place to rise until doubled (about 1 hour).
Knead again.
Shape into 2 loaves and let rise again until light (about 1/2 hour).
Bake for about 45 minutes at 375°.
Turn out of pans and brush with melted butter.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Mix together in large pot and bring to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes without stirring.
Add 1/2 teaspoon soda and 1 teaspoon vanilla. (Add 1 1/2 cups peanuts, if desired.) Pour over 6 quarts popped corn.
Stir well.
Spread in large flat pan.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: fresh cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Cut cauliflower into bite size flowerets.
Cut and stem broccoli, using tops only.
Add the sliced onion.
Mix last 3 ingredients.
Pour over vegetables and toss lightly.
Refrigerate and let stand 3 to 4 hours before serving.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together sugars and Crisco.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well after each addition.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° 12-15 minutes.
Yield:
4-1/2 dozen.

title: frankfurter casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In frypan, saute onion and celery in butter until tender.
Stir in franks, mustard, soup and water. Prepare muffin mix as label directs.
Let batter rest for 5 minutes.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with sour cream.
Beat after each addition.
Grease and flour 2 (8-inch) round pans.
Put 1/4 of batter in each pan and sprinkle with 1/4 of topping (below).
Add remaining batter and sprinkle with rest of topping.
Bake at 325 ° for 35 to 40 minutes.
May also use 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: vegetarian meatballs
directions: Reconstitute Granburger in boiling water.
Mix together with all other ingredients.
Form into walnut-size balls and fry in heated oil.
Can be frozen for later use.
To serve, bake in gravy 20 minutes.

title: "leftovers" monday's meat pie
directions: Brown celery, onion and green pepper in hot fat.
Add and combine meat, potatoes, carrots and peas.
Add gravy and season to taste.
Pour into casserole; top with bread cubes browned in butter.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: bacon wrapped shrimp and water chestnuts
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: hazel's special
directions: Brown hamburg and saute onion.
Add soups and half of grated cheese.
Mix with cooked noodles and top with grated cheese.
Put in greased casserole and bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: pumpkin nut muffins
directions: Mix well. Bake in 350° oven for 20-25 minutes.

title: easy pineapple salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar together.
Add large can drained pineapple tidbits.
Add 12 oz. cool whip.
Stir well and serve. Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: crab pate
directions: Heat soup on low without adding any liquid to it.
In the meantime, prepare unflavored gelatin with the 3 tablespoons of water.
Remove hot soup from burner and add the gelatin, cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Blend well and fold in the peppers, celery, onion and crab meat.
Oil the sides of a mold and pour the mixture into the mold.
Refrigerate overnight or until firm.
Unmold on plate and garnich as desired.

title: easy cream cheese pie
directions: In medium mixing bowl, blend cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
(You may wish to microwave for 40 seconds to make it quicker.)
Pour this into pie crust and spread evenly.
Add fruit of your choice (i.e. small can crushed drained pineapple or small can drained mandarin oranges).
Put in layer and then top with Cool Whip.
Garnish with crushed nuts of your choice and freeze. Remove from freezer 1 hour before needed.
Don't be shy, use more than one type of fruit.

title: old fashioned pot roast
directions: Cook at 325°.
Trim excess fat.
Place in 4-quart Dutch oven or casserole; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add onions, broth, paprika, allspice and bay leaves.
Cover; bake for 2 hours.
Add carrots and potatoes.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes longer, until vegetables are tender.
Remove bay leaves.
In small bowl combine cornstarch and water.
Stir into hot liquid.
Bake 15 minutes longer or until gravy is thickened.
Believe it or not this recipe is very low in fat.

title: after the game spaghetti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef and bacon; drain. Add tomatoes, Ro-Tel and green chilies, mushrooms, olives and onion to ground beef.
Mix.
Stir in cheese and spaghetti. Crumble bacon over top.
Place ingredients in 3-quart casserole. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: company potatoes
directions: Mix hash brown potatoes, cream of chicken soup, sour cream, Cheddar cheese, onion and 1/4 cup of butter.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan, sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle cornflakes over top with the other 1/4 cup of butter.
Bake 1 hour, covered, in 350° oven. Uncover and bake for additional 1/2 hour.
Serve hot.

title: cherry chiffon dessert
directions: Combine all ingredients, fold in mini marshmallows.
Chill for 1/2 hour or more.

title: chinatown spaghetti
directions: Brown hamburger, onions and celery.
Drain fat.
Add Chinese vegetables, tomato soup (no water), soy sauce and spices.
Mix with spaghetti.
Place all in a casserole and bake 30 to 45 minutes in 350° oven (cover with foil while baking).
Do not add any cheese to this dish.

title: peggy's maple nut squares
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan or spray with Pam.
Mix flour with sugar.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing with a spoon.
Spread into pan.
Bake 45 minutes.
Do not open oven door while baking.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots until slightly fork-tender.
Mix all liquid ingredients and the seasonings together.
Arrange in layers the carrots, onion and pepper.
Pour liquid over all.
This is best if made several days in advance.
Liquid can be kept and used up to two weeks in the refrigerator.
I use fresh carrots.

title: fruit dip i
directions: Mix well and serve with fresh sliced fruit.

title: black bean soup 1
directions: Combine beans, water and salt pork in Dutch oven or large heavy stockpot.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 2 1/2 hours or until beans are tender.
Combine mustard with warm water in cup; let stand 5 minutes for flavor to develop.
Add mustard water to cooked beans along with onion, pepper flakes, garlic, oregano, cumin and black pepper.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes longer or until beans are tender.
(If soup is too thick, add more water.)
Stir in lemon juice and salt.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes.
Garnish with hard-cooked egg, if desired.

title: children's bird seed
directions: Mix equal amounts in a large bowl.
Serve as a snack.

title: light lemon squares
directions: Mix cake flour and 1/4 cup confectioners sugar.
Cut in cream cheese until crumbly.
Gradually add oil, stirring with fork.
Toss with fingertips until evenly moistened.
Press in bottom of 8-inch square pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: garden herb chicken
directions: Cook noodles. Saute tomatoes in oil with onions until soft. Add chicken, water and bouillon; bring to a boil. Reduce heat, add cream cheese and cook until cheese is smooth; about 2 minutes. Serve over noodles.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix ingredients until smooth.
Chill at least two hours and serve with raw vegetables.
Tasty on baked potatoes, too!

title: cream puffs
directions: Add butter to water; heat until butter melts.
Add flour all at once and stir vigorously until ball forms in center of pan. Remove from fire and let stand 5 minutes.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after adding each egg.
Mixture should be very stiff.
Makes 8 large puffs, 18 small ones or 36 hors d'oeuvre size.
Shape on buttered cookie sheet by dropping from spoon. Bake until free from beads of moisture (40 to 45 minutes) in moderately hot oven, 375°.
Fill with whipped cream.

title: sage tea
directions: In an Earthenware teapot, place tea leaves, sage, mint and sugar.
Stir until sugar is well blended.
Pour in boiling water. Stir again.
Cover and brew 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve in tea glasses with lemon on side.
Makes 4 to 5 teacups

title: lemon sauce
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix flour and sugar and add to beaten eggs.
If mixture is too thick to stir, add a little water.
Pour boiling water over the mixture a cupful at a time until you have used 5 cups.
Cook over medium heat until slightly thickened, beating with a rotary beater while cooking.
Add the butter while it is hot.
Add flavoring and salt.
Serve warm or cold.

title: broccoli-cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook vegetables about 5 to 7 minutes.
Drain.
Combine all ingredients except topping and pour over cooked vegetables in baking dish.
Sprinkle topping over casserole and drizzle 2/3 stick melted butter or margarine over topping.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry jello salad
directions: Combine jello mix with water until dissolved; add fruit and chill until soft set.
Fold in Cool Whip; chill 2 hours or overnight.
Makes a 9 x 13-inch serving dish full.

title: macadamia almond brittle
directions: Combine sugar and corn syrup in a 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Stir in nuts.
Microwave on High for 4 to 5 minutes or until a candy thermometer reads 300° (hard crack stage).
Quickly stir in butter, vanilla and baking soda until mixture is light and foamy.
When bubbles subside, pour onto a greased cookie sheet, spreading as thinly as possible with a metal spatula.
Cool completely; break into pieces.
Store in an airtight container with waxed paper between layers.
Yields about 1 pound.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: quick cookies
directions: Mix ingredients and drop onto greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large mixing bowl.
Then bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook for 30 minutes until you put toothpick in it and when it doesn't have anything on it, cake is done.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli as directed and drain well.
Spread into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with sliced chicken. Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry together and spread on top of chicken. Sprinkle bread crumbs on top and then top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Mix flour, cornmeal, salt and pepper.
Dredge tomato slices in cornmeal mixture.
Fry in hot drippings or melted shortening until brown, turning only once.
Drain well on paper towels.
Serve hot.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash cooked sweet potatoes and add butter, orange juice, 3/4 cup brown sugar, eggs and cinnamon. Mix and refrigerate.
When ready to use, prepare topping.
Mix together pecans, butter and 1/2 cup brown sugar.
Smooth on top.
Bake 30-40 minutes at 350°. Serves 6-8 depending on amount of sweet potatoes used.

title: forgotten meringues
directions: Beat egg whites with salt until foamy; add cream of tartar and beat until whites form a peak.
Add sugar, one tablespoon at a time, beating at high speed for about 15 minutes.
Add vanilla. Drop into buttered glass oven dish
(8 x 12-inch pan or 9-inch pie pan) and place in preheated 400° oven.
Turn off heat and leave meringues overnight.
Do not look until morning.
To serve, cover with any fruit and whipped sweetened cream.

title: low-fat corn chips
directions: With a pastry brush, spread tortilla very lightly with water. Sprinkle with salt.
Cut each tortilla in 6 triangles.
Repeat with other tortillas.
Place on cookie sheet and bake until crispy in 425° oven (about 5 minutes).
Remove and let cool.

title: corn pone
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream oleo and sugar with eggs.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk; mix together. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: a meal in one
directions: Brown hamburger. While hamburger is browning, boil potatoes. After draining hamburger, add green beans and tomato soup.
Stir together well and simmer until hot all through.
Put in casserole dish.
Mash potatoes and season.
Spread on top of mixture.
Lay slices of cheese on top and let melt.
Ready to eat.

title: soy roasted nuts
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Spread the nuts on baking sheet and bake for 5 minutes.
Drizzle soy sauce on nuts and stir well. Return baking sheet to oven for 5 more minutes.
Turn off oven. Stir nuts again and leave them in oven for a final 5 minutes. (Nuts will become dry and crisp.) Allow nuts to cool.
Store in covered container to retain their crispness.

title: frozen corn
directions: Cook corn 5 minutes then cool.
Put into containers and freeze.

title: hot rolls
directions: Stir first 4 ingredients and add sugar and salt; mix. Dissolve dry yeast in 1 cup warm potato water.
Mix in.
Cover and let rise 2 hours.
Then add flour.
Let rise 2 more hours. Punch down and make out rolls.
Put on buttered baking pan or in buttered muffin tins.
Let rise until doubled in size.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes or so.
Butter tops.

title: cowboy stew
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Add all canned ingredients (juice and all).
Heat through.
Serve over rice or with crackers.

title: onion ring batter
directions: Stir flour, baking powder and salt in a bowl; drop egg yolk in center.
Add water and oil.
Mix well.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into flour mixture.
Dip onion rings into batter and fry in hot oil until brown.
This batter is good on shrimp or mushrooms, also.

title: potato corn chowder
directions: Cook green pepper and onion in saucepan coated with vegetable cooking spray over medium heat, stirring constantly, 5 minutes or until tender.
Stir in chicken broth, potatoes, salt and pepper. Bring to boil and simmer 5 to 7 minutes until potatoes are tender.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon of milk and sugar in a large bowl until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping.
Spread on bottom of crust.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven for about 40 minutes.

title: angel food cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Sift flour and 1/2 cup sugar 4 times, set aside.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add cream of tartar and salt; beat until soft peaks form.
Add remaining sugar 2 tablespoons at a time, beating well after each.
Fold in vanilla. Sprinkle the flour and sugar mixture over the egg whites, 1/2 cup at a time.
Gently fold in dry ingredients with a spatula.
Pour the batter into ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake 1 hour.

title: tuna bake for twelve
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Add 2 tablespoons butter and 1/2 cup milk.
In saucepan, melt 4 tablespoons butter.
Blend in flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Add 3 cups milk.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in gravy, tuna, pimiento and noodles.
Spread in a 13 1/2 x 8 3/4 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 25 minutes.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter; toss with crumbs and cheese.
Sprinkle on casserole.
Bake until heated through, 10 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: grilled shrimp in shells
directions: Remove legs from shrimp, but do not peel.
Cut several lengthwise slits along inner curve of each shrimp and insert a few small sprigs of rosemary.
In a large bowl whisk together garlic, oil and lemon juice.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Toss shrimp in marinade, coating well.
Add more rosemary sprigs and lemon slices.
Marinate one to two hours.
Drain shrimp and place on grill.
Grill 3 min. on each side or until opaque.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip together.
Pour into graham cracker pie crust and top with the cherry pie filling. Chill until ready to eat.

title: tex mex dip
directions: Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco mix.
Put bean dip in bottom of dish.
Cover with sour cream mixture.
Add olives, onion and tomatoes in layers.
Top with grated cheese.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Heat pineapple and jello until jello is dissolved.
Add cream cheese and baby food.
Mix well.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.
Stir in Cool Whip and mix well.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: peanut patties
directions: Mix together sugar, water and syrup and bring to a boil.
Add peanuts.
Cook to 265°.
Remove from heat and add milk.
Stir until dull.
Add a little red cake coloring for color.
Drop on wax paper.
Make any size you wish.

title: earthquake cake #1
directions: Follow directions on cake mix box.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Cover bottom of pan with coconut and spread with nuts.
Pour prepared cake mix over top.
Mix cream cheese, butter and sugar, spoon over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Place on larger pan for serving.

title: frosting
directions: Cook flour and milk until very thick, stirring constantly. Cool.
Cream sugar and butter until very fluffy.
Add vanilla and blend with first cooled mixture (should be consistency of whipped cream).
Delicious on any spice cake.

title: shrimp bisque
directions: In saucepan, combine celery, potato, onion, water, salt and dash of pepper.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender, stirring occasionally. Blend milk and flour; stir into potato mixture.
Add shrimp and butter.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Garnish with snipped parsley, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tomato soup salad dressing
directions: Combine in quart jar.
Shake well and refrigerate.

title: one-pan potatoes and chicken teriyaki
directions: While potatoes cook in large skillet, toss and brown chicken in oil over high heat for 5 minutes.
Add potatoes; saute and toss until potatoes are lightly browned.
Add onions and teriyaki sauce; toss until heated through.
Makes 4 servings.
Per serving: 280 calories and 9 g. fat.

title: grandma's gingerbread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients. Melt margarine in the boiling water.
Add egg and dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake in a 9 x 9 or 8 x 8-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: billie's chocolate chip cookie
directions: Mix margarine, oil and vanilla.
Add sugar to mixture.
Add eggs, one at a time, until blended.
Add dry ingredients to mixture and then chocolate chips.
Drop batter by rounded teaspoon and bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: pineapple pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown chops about 10 minutes on each side, then arrange in single layer in shallow baking dish.
Melt butter in skillet; add drained pineapple.
Stir over low heat until brown glaze in pan dissolved.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour pineapple mixture over chops and bake covered for 30 minutes. Reduce heat to 325°.
Bake 30 minutes.
Add liquid from pineapple. Bake 15 minutes or until chops are very tender.

title: ginger bell cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Mix in egg and molasses.
Sift and measure flour.
Sift again with spices.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Mix well.

title: corn relish
directions: To prepare corn, boil 5 minutes. Cut from cob, combine with remaining ingredients. Simmer 20 minutes; bring to boil. Pack boiling hot into jars and seal.

title: best ever brownies
directions: Melt chocolate in margarine. Beat eggs; add all other ingredients. Spread mixture in greased 8-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool before cutting.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix
all
ingredients thoroughly; roll into balls.
Bake at 350°
for
about
8 minutes on ungreased baking sheet.
Let cool 1 minute and remove from pan.

title: spanish eggplant
directions: Combine eggplant, onion, green pepper and bacon drippings; mix well and let stand 10 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, salt and sugar. Place in a medium saucepan.
Cover and cook 5 to 10 minutes over low heat.
Spoon mixture into a greased, shallow 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with breadcrumbs and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken.
The batter will be thin. Pour over chicken and bake in a 350° oven until hot.

title: chocolate banana snack cake
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Make a well in center of dry ingredients.
Add milk, banana, butter, lemon juice and vanilla.
Beat with a fork until well blended, about 2 minutes.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour into a greased 9-inch square cake pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes or until done.
Cool completely.
Dust with icing sugar.

title: pecan pie cookies
directions: Melt the oleo in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch square pan.
Mix the flour, brown sugar and baking powder.
Pour the melted oleo over the mixture.
Mix well, then pat firmly into the greased pan. Bake about 10 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream together sugar, butter and eggs. Add pumpkin, flour, and spices. Mix thoroughly. Fold chocolate chips into batter. Pour into loaf pan or 4 mini loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Grease a 1-quart casserole dish.
Add eggs and beat with a fork.
Mix in sugar and flour until well-blended with eggs.
Add pineapple, stirring well.
Place bread pieces on top of casserole dish.
Slice butter into pats on top of casserole.
Cover.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or longer.
Serve as a side dish with chicken or ham.

title: skinny soup
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil and simmer for 30 minutes. Eat 3 times a day. In 3 days you could lose up to 5 to 10 pounds. Results may vary.

title: crunchy cookies
directions: Melt one cup of Baker's Semi-Sweet Chocolate Chips over hot water.
Beat 2 egg whites with a dash of salt until foamy. Gradually add 1/2 cup sugar, beating well.
Then beat until stiff peaks will form.

title: chicken and squash casserole
directions: Butter a large casserole.
Line with dressing.
Place squash in casserole. Top with mixture.
Add Pepperidge Farm dressing. Dot with margarine. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: molasses jar-filler cookies
directions: Measure flour, sifted with spices.
Mix first five items in a large bowl.
Mix coffee and soda in a 1/2-cup measure.
Fill with cold water.
Stir.
Add to first five items.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Chill in refrigerator.
Roll 1/4-inch thick and cut out cookies.
Bake on greased cookie sheet.

title: italian pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat for 20 minutes. Put in cold oven. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese and bacon flavored cheese.
Cheddar may be softened or chopped in food processor.
Chop dried beef and onion. Combine all together.
Shape into balls and chill.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: bits of brickle cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients until crumbly; set 1/2 cup aside.
Add rest of ingredients; mix.
Put in a greased, floured sheet pan. Put 1/2 cup mix that was set aside on top.
Brown almonds on top of mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: holiday rum balls
directions: In a large bowl, combine wafer crumbs, 1 cup sugar, walnuts, rum, corn syrup and butter.
Knead together; roll into 1-inch balls and then coat in remaining confectioners sugar.
Arrange on a baking sheet.
Cover well with plastic wrap and let sit for 48 hours.
Serves enough for a party.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Heat oven
to
Cook chicken breasts until almost done and drain.	Shred or chunk the chicken and layer in a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.

title: macaroni pie
directions: Toss cooked macaroni in cooking oil in a large bowl.
Combine all other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: black beans and rice
directions: Soak and cook beans as directed on package.
When beans are done, add tomatoes.
Saute onion.
Add to beans and tomatoes.
Add rice to it (rice has to be cooked).
Salt and pepper to taste. Add garlic powder to taste.
Simmer on low for about 30 minutes.

title: cherry delight
directions: Pour filling in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle cake mix over filling.
Pour melted butter over cake mix.
Sprinkle nuts over top and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix beef and ingredients all but sauce ingredients.
Shape in loaf pan.
Score loaf mixture by making grooves across top.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Sprinkle chicken generously with hot sauce and salt to taste, then coat with flour, leaving wings in excess flour for 30 minutes. Fry until crispy.
(Remember, frying tones down hot sauce.)
This dish is great for lunch, snacks or hors d'oeuvres.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix ingredients.
Layer dressing, chicken and dressing in casserole dish.
Cook, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 45 minutes, until brown around edges.

title: bread pudding
directions: Beat egg whites lightly.
Mix all ingredients and bake until done in a 350° oven.
