title: frozen dessert
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into refrigerator dish and freeze until firm.
Cut into 24 squares.

title: texas candy cake
directions: Mix the chopped fruit with the tablespoon of flour.
Stir in the chopped pecans, flaked coconut and the can of condensed milk. Preheat the oven to 250°.
Grease and flour a tube pan.
Press mixture into pan and bake 1 1/2 hours.
Allow the cake to cool and wrap tightly in cheesecloth.
Refrigerate at least 2 weeks.
Makes about 24 thin slices.

title: shrimp or crab meat
directions: Mix milk, shrimp and cream cheese together.
Add onion, horseradish and Worcestershire sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes with a top on dish.
After 20 minutes, put bread crumbs and grated cheese on top and bake for 10 minutes remaining.
Serve with crackers, Melba toast or bagel chips.

title: quick coffee cake
directions: Cream white sugar and butter.
Add eggs; beat until creamy. Sift flour, baking powder and salt thoroughly.
Add to sugar mixture.
Add milk and vanilla; mix well.
Spread batter evenly in large cookie sheet.
In separate bowl, mix brown sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over batter.
Dot batter with butter.
Bake in oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: strawberry and pretzel jello salad
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients and pack in bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 8 minutes at 400°.
Cool.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Place 4 chicken breasts at bottom. Mix chicken soup and juice. Pour over chicken. Put slice of Swiss cheese on top of each piece of chicken.
Top with herb stuffing mix and 1/4 cup melted butter.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool 15 minutes before serving.
Serves 4.

title: egg nog
directions: For best results, use a blender or hand shaker.
Blend all 30 to 60 seconds.
Pour into 2 glasses.
Garnish with nutmeg.

title: tap dancers tators
directions: Pare and cut potatoes into quarters.
Combine flour, cheese, salt and pepper in a plastic bag.
Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan. Shake potatoes in mixtures
in bag.
Lay in pan and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: In large salad bowl, fill half full with shredded lettuce and spinach.
Layer celery, green pepper, red onion and cooled peas. Spread mayonnaise over peas.
Top with cheese.
Sprinkle with bacon bits.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.

title: cracker snackers
directions: Mix dill weed, dressing and oil. Then mix dry ingredients together. Pour oil mix over cracker mix in large bowl. Stir.

title: creamy macaroni casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese dinner as directed, except use 3/4 cup milk.
Saute onion and green pepper in margarine until tender. Combine with remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine dry pudding mix and pineapple.
Fold in rest of ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight or until well chilled.

title: sugared nuts
directions: Preheat oven to 225°.
Beat the egg white with 1 tablespoon water; stir nuts in it.
Stir this mixture in the mixed sugar, salt and cinnamon; spread on a cookie sheet.
Bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Let cool and store in the refrigerator.

title: jellied meat loaf
directions: Run the veal or chicken, celery and green pepper through meat grinder.

title: rosemary pizza
directions: Add yeast and sugar to cup of water; mix well.
Make well with flour.
Add mixed egg, oil, salt and yeast mixture.
Knead well (cover and raise).
Spread 2 tablespoons oil to a 12 x 18-inch cookie sheet.
Punch down dough and spread on cookie sheet. Sprinkle 2 tablespoons olive oil over top of dough.
Sprinkle black pepper and crushed rosemary on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: layer cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cake mix, water, applesauce and egg whites.
Beat until moistened.
Beat 2 minutes at high speed. Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until done.
Cool, then remove.
When cool, frost.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: My favorite is huckleberry, but any fruit will do!

title: tasty fruit freeze
directions: Combine all ingredients; pour into muffin tins lined with baking cups.
Once frozen, remove from muffin tins and store in Ziploc bags in the freezer.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Put cream cheese in mixing bowl. Cream and add powdered sugar. Beat in peanut butter. Mix until all ingredients are incorporated. Fold in Cool Whip. Spread into pie shell. Chill for 2 to 3 hours.

title: popover chicken tarragon
directions: Brown chicken
pieces
in the 2 tablespoons of hot oil; season with a little salt and pepper.
Place chicken pieces in a well-greased
x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
In mixing bowl, beat eggs.
Blend
in
1/2 cups of milk and 1 tablespoon of oil. Stir
together the flour, salt and tarragon.
Add to egg mixture; beat until smooth.	Pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° until done, 55 to 60 minutes.

title: strawberry pretzel
directions: Mix and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan; bake 10 minutes at 400°. Cool.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender.
Cool and remove from bones; cut up into bite sizes.
Boil vegetables in hot water for 8 to 10 minutes, then drain.
Combine chicken, vegetables, chicken soup, celery soup, water, onion and pepper.
Pour into a large casserole dish.

title: spaghetti pie(low-fat)
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain.
Mix in butter, Parmesan cheese and egg.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Spread in casserole to form a crust.
Saute beef, onion and pepper.
Stir in spaghetti sauce, sugar, oregano and garlic salt.
Spread Ricotta over spaghetti layer.
Top with meat sauce mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle Mozzarella on top and bake 10 more minutes.

title: barbecued beaver
directions: Place beaver in a medium baking dish.
Cover beaver with barbecue sauce.
Add salt and pepper and bake for 2 hours at 350°.

title: rice-vegetable burgers
directions: Mix rice, parsley and carrots.
Add spices.
Mix in flour and egg.
Fry in coated nonstick vegetable sprayed pan or grill. Serve on toasted whole wheat buns with condiments.
Serves 6.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix jello in boiling water until dissolved; cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill.

title: marshmallow fudge
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Boil until mixture forms soft ball (stir constantly).
(I always use a candy thermometer.)
Add marshmallow cream and chocolate chips and stir until completely blended.
Put in lightly buttered pan.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Cook, crumble and drain sausage.
Butter bread and cut into cubes.
Place cubed bread in a large greased casserole dish. Sprinkle sausage and shredded Longhorn cheese over bread.
Combine eggs, half and half, salt and mustard.
Beat well.
Pour over sausage.
Chill for 8 hours.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. Serves 6.

title: silver fish omelette
directions: Break and beat 2 eggs until nice and fluffy.
Add leftover Silver Fish Adobo.
Heat 1 tablespoon cooking oil in shallow frying pan.
Add silver fish/egg mixture.
Cook over medium heat for 2 minutes on one side.
Turn over and cook for another 2 minutes, until golden brown.
Remove from pan and serve.
Good with steamed or fried rice or as filling for sandwich.

title: lemon snow pudding
directions: Sift together the first 3 ingredients.
Blend together the egg yolks, lemon juice, milk and lemon rind.
Combine liquid with dry ingredients; beat until mixed.
Fold in the egg whites, stiffly beaten.
Pour into greased casserole and place in pan of hot water.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: grilled pork chops
directions: Place the thick pork chops in a glass baking dish in a single layer.
Sprinkle each chop generously with Creole seasoning (only on the side that is up in the dish).
Cover tightly with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Place on grill.
Cook until done, turning only once.
Do not overcook or they will be too dry.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Debone and cut into bite size pieces.
Cook noodles in chicken broth until tender; drain.
Add chicken to noodles.
Add soups and sour cream.
Pour into casserole dish and top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Cook in 400° oven until brown.

title: hangover eggs
directions: Cover bottom of glass 8 x 8-inch pan with croutons.
Add grated cheese carefully.
Mix together butter, flour, baking powder and salt.
Add eggs, cottage cheese and chiles.
Spoon carefully over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until set.

title: meringue
directions: Beat egg whites with cream of tartar, salt and extract until foamy.
Continue beating, adding sugar, one tablespoon at a time. Be sure sugar is dissolved.

title: sweet-sour kielbasa
directions: Slice kielbasa into bite-size and place in roasting pan. Sprinkle Jell-O over the kielbasa.
Cover with jelly.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Drain juice and serve with toothpicks.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion; add soup.
Layer mixture with Tater Tots.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Top with cheese and return to oven until cheese melts.

title: melting moments(cookies)
directions: For icing and may be colored with food coloring.

title: meat loaf
directions: Beat egg slightly.
Add catsup, seasoning, green pepper and onion.
Mix beef and crumbs.
Add other mixture and knead until well blended.
Shape into loaf and bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: pumpkin chess pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter until fluffy.
Add meal, salt, creamer and eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add pumpkin and spices and mix well.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: mushroom meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape into loaf or pack lightly in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: fat-free sweet potato corn muffins
directions: Combine flour, cornmeal and baking powder and stir to mix well.
Add the sweet potato, juice, molasses and egg whites.
Stir until moistened.
Fold in raisins or dates.
Coat muffin tins with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: crumb cake
directions: Combine.
Pour batter in 12 x 18 x 1-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove.
Put crumbs on top and bake 20 minutes more.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream margarine and beat in sugar. Add eggs one at a time and bananas. Sift flour with baking powder and soda. Stir flour into egg mixture and add vanilla. Fold in sour cream and nuts. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool and frost with butter cream or cream cheese frosting.

title: creamy coconut pie
directions: Beat cream cheese in mixer bowl until softened; beat in sugar. Gradually add milk and beat until smooth.
Fold in coconut and whipped topping.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm.

title: kahlua
directions: Dissolve coffee in hot water.
Add sugar and heat until dissolved and clear.
Cool.
Add vodka or brandy.
Add vanilla bean or extract.
Put in crock or jar.
Age 30 days.
Best if stored in dark bottle or cover jar with aluminum foil.

title: sister lucy's layer dessert
directions: Mix the pecans, oleo and flour well.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients except nutmeg in large bowl.
Mix well.
Place in a greased casserole.
Sprinkle with nutmeg on top. Set casserole in a pan of water.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake 90 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: pecan ritz torte
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and bake in an 8-inch pan for 20 minutes at 350°.
Drain the pineapple and add to the whipped cream. Serve on top of torte.
For double amount bake for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken (cut up) for 1 hour until tender.
Cool and cut up in small, bite-size pieces.
Spread on bottom of casserole dish (rectangular).
Mix the chicken soup and sour cream.
Spread over chicken.
Crush Ritz crackers, mix with celery seed and spread over soup mixture.
Sprinkle top with melted margarine.
Bake about 40 minutes, or until bubbly at 350°.

title: caesar salad
directions: Mash garlic; add to salad oil.
Break lettuce in salad bowl; tear endive.
Add croutons, anchovy and tomatoes.
Strain oil to remove garlic; pour over vegetables.
Combine remaining ingredients; beat well.
Pour over salad; toss lightly.
Garnish with ripe olives.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: italian salad dressing
directions: Mix, blend and chill all ingredients.

title: apple pie-deep dish style
directions: Stir together
sugar, flour, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt; mix with apples.
Turn	into
x
9 x 2-inch baking pan, dot with butter.
Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry for one crust pie. Fold pastry in half; cut slits near center.
Unfold over fruit in pan; fold
edges until just inside edge of pan.
Bake 1 hour or until juice begins to bubble through slits in crust. Best served warm.

title: freezing cucumbers
directions: Make syrup of sugar, water, vinegar and salt.
Cook syrup until dissolved and clear, let cool and pour over sliced, unpeeled cucumbers in freezer containers.
Freeze.

title: japanese chicken noodle soup
directions: Bring chicken to a boil in large saucepan.
Add enough reserved mushroom liquid to make 5 cups of broth.
Simmer, covered, for 5 minutes.
Add mushrooms, soy sauce and noodles. Stir well.
Simmer 3 to 4 minutes.
Divide sliced chicken into 4 soup bowls; pour soup over and garnish with thin slice of lemon and serve.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix ingredients in large bowl.
Pour into baking pan and smooth out. Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Top will be light brown when done.
Slice into squares to serve.

title: milk chocolate peanut butter bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, mix peanut butter and butter; beat until smooth.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla; beat until creamy.
Blend in flour and salt.
Stir in 1 cup chocolate morsels.
Spread into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until edges brown.
Sprinkle with remaining milk chocolate. Let stand 5 minutes until chocolate becomes shiny and soft.
Spread chocolate evenly over top.
Cool completely.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch bars.
Makes 48 bars.

title: spaghetti sauce dip
directions: Blend sour cream and spaghetti sauce.
Serve with corn chips or potato chips.

title: taco dish
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain.
Add 1/3 of taco seasoning.
Set aside.
Mix cream cheese and sour cream.
Spread mixture on the bottom of baking dish (2 quarts).
Sprinkle another 1/3 of taco seasoning over mixture.
Spread beef, lettuce, tomato and cheese over top of mixture.
Sprinkle remaining taco seasoning on top. Let cool in refrigerator.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: cream of asparagus soup
directions: Melt butter in a 4-quart pan.
Add onion and cook slowly just until soft and golden; do not brown.
Add chicken stock and bring to a boil.
Meanwhile, cut tips (about 3 inches in length) off asparagus and set aside.
In processor or blend or by hand, slice butt ends into 1/4-inch pieces.
Drop pieces into boiling broth. Cover and boil gently until very soft, about 30 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes, then puree soup in blender or processor.
Return soup to pan.
Add asparagus tips and simmer until just tender, about 5 minutes.
Stir in cream.
Season with salt and pepper and a drop or two of lemon juice.
Serve warm or cold.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Rinse in cold water.
Brown meat and drain.
Add seasonings and tomato sauce; simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and combine cottage cheese, sour cream, onions and lasagna noodles.
Alternate layers of noodles with meat mixture in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Top with shredded cheese. Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in 13 x 9-inch buttered casserole.
Top with crushed corn flakes; dot with margarine. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: heart and soul tea
directions: Combine 2 cups of the water and the sugar in a saucepan.
Cook until sugar dissolves; set aside.
In a 4-quart pitcher or bowl, pour the boiling water over the tea bags.
Let stand 5 minutes. Remove tea bags.
Add the remaining 8 cups of water, the sugar syrup, lemonade concentrate, vanilla and almond extracts.
Serve over ice.
Garnish with fresh peaches.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar and syrup in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Stir in nuts; microwave on High for 3 to 5 minutes or until light brown.
Add butter and vanilla and mix well.
Microwave on High again for 1 to 2 minutes.
Peanuts will be lightly brown.
Add baking soda and stir until light and foamy. Pour mixture onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Let cool 1/2 to 1 hour.
When cool, break into pieces.
(Total time, microwave time is 8 to 11 minutes.)

title: dried beef casserole
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan.
Add onion and pepper.
Cook until tender, about 5 minutes on low heat. Cut dried beef into small pieces.
Add to onion mixture and continue cooking until browned. Stir in soup, milk, pepper and paprika.
Heat to boiling.
Cook macaroni as directed; do not add salt. Drain macaroni and rinse. Drain again.
Combine with beef sauce.
Pour into casserole. Spread well with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix milk, eggs and mustard.

title: beef and broccoli
directions: Slice beef into very thin strips.
In skillet over medium-high heat, heat oil.
Add beef and stir fry until browned and juices evaporate.
Add soup, soy, vinegar, garlic and pepper flakes.
Heat to a boil.
Add broccoli and cook over medium heat until broccoli is tender-crisp, stirring often.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: favorite lemon cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat just until blended.
Pour into a greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, until toothpick comes out clean.
While warm cake is still in pan, poke holes in it with toothpick and drizzle half the Lemon Glaze on it.
Turn out of pan and drizzle again over top.

title: herbed vegetables
directions: Slice celery
on
the
diagonal
into
pieces
about
1 1/2-inch thick.
Cut
the zucchini in half lengthwise and then cut into
1/2-inch slices.
Remove seeds and membrane from the bell peppers
and cut into diagonal pieces about 1-inch.
Heat oil in a heavy skillet over medium-high heat.
Add the celery to stir-fry until barely tender.
Add zucchini and peppers and stir-fry
until all
vegetables
are crisp-tender.
Add salt, pepper and oregano.
Cook
for
seconds
longer.
Stir in chives.	Serve immediately.

title: spinach loaf
directions: Mix ingredients well, then beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold egg whites into loaf mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 8 servings.

title: date nut balls
directions: In medium saucepan, combine margarine, dates, cherries and sugar.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture becomes a soft paste.
Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies cereal and pecans.
Mix thoroughly.
Portion out by level tablespoon onto wax paper or buttered baking sheet.
Shape into balls.
Let stand until cool.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar, milk and Cool Whip together until smooth.
Pour over cake.
Pour pie filling on top.

title: jiffy barbecue sauce
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate and use on ribs, steaks, hamburgers, etc. before grilling.

title: oven-fried potatoes
directions: Preheat a broiler.
Cover a broiling pan with aluminum foil. In a bowl, combine the egg with the seasonings and stir to combine. Dip the potato pieces into the egg mixture and place on the prepared pan.
Broil 4 to 6 inches from direct heat for 8 to 10 minutes per side or until crispy on the outside and cooked through on the inside.
Serve hot.
Serves 4.

title: chicken tandoori(india)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Rinse chicken pieces under cold water. Peel garlic clove and finely chop.
Arrange chicken pieces skin side up in shallow baking pan.
Pour butter or margarine over them.
Sprinkle the chicken with the onion, garlic, green peppers, tomatoes, salt, curry powder, coriander, cumin, turmeric, cinnamon and black pepper.
Dissolve 2 chicken bouillon cubes in 2 cups water.
(You can also use canned chicken broth, chicken stock or water.)
Add the liquid to the baking pan and place pan in preheated oven for 50 minutes.
Serve on steamed rice, if desired.

title: quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat eggs; stir in milk, cream, salt, pepper and Tabasco.
Place cheese and onion in pie crust.
Pour egg mixture over cheese.
Bake for 50 to 55 minutes in 375° oven.

title: mom's peas and macaroni
directions: Chop onion and fry in olive oil until lightly browned.
Add tomato sauce, water, bay leaves and salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil and simmer 10 minutes.
Bring water to a boil in 2-quart saucepan for macaroni; cook until tender.
Drain and rinse, then add to sauce mixture.
Cook peas until tender and drain.
Add to mixture.
Serve in large bowl and sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: london broil
directions: Place London broil in a lasagna pan.
Add Italian salad dressing and add Mrs. Dash and Jane's Krazy salt.
Marinate overnight in the refrigerator.
Place in broiler and cook to preference.
Use salad dressing as a gravy.
Great with Bill's mashed potatoes.

title: carrot bake
directions: Peel, slice, steam and mash carrots.
Saute pepper and onion in 4 tablespoons butter.
Stir in flour, milk, salt and sugar. Cook until thickened.
Add carrots and put in greased casserole dish.
Melt 1 tablespoon butter and add bread crumbs.
Cook until browned.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Cream eggs, sugar and cooking oil.
Sift together the flour, soda and salt.
Add pineapple alternately with flour mixture to creamed mixture.
Beat well after each addition, then add vanilla and pecans.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini and onion together for 5 minutes. Drain. Combine soup and sour cream.
Stir in carrots, then fold in zucchini and onions.
Mix butter with stuffing mix.
Spread half of stuffing mix in bottom of 8 x 13-inch pan.

title: refrigerator scones
directions: Warm buttermilk to 125°. Combine 5 cups flour, yeast and sugar in mixing bowl. Add milk and mix 1 minute.
Turn off mixer.
Add salt, baking powder, soda, oil and eggs. Turn on mixer and add remaining flour, one cup at a time, until dough begins to clean the sides of the bowl. Dough should be soft.
If it gets too stiff, drizzle a little warm water over dough as you mix to soften. Dough can be used immediately or covered and stored in refrigerator up to 2 to 3 weeks.
Dough will continue to rise in refrigerator.
Knead down.
Roll dough onto lightly floured surface. Cut into shapes.
Let rise. Cook on griddle at 375°, turning when browned.

title: spooky spiders(makes 20)
directions: Cover a baking sheet with waxed paper.
In a small saucepan, over very low heat, melt chips.
Stir until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Stir in noodles and, if desired, nuts until coated.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Chill 15 minutes or until firm. Remove from refrigerator.
Store loosely in a cool place.

title: tangier crab cakes
directions: Mix all dry ingredients, except bread, together.
Add beaten egg and other wet ingredients.
Add crumbled bread and mix lightly.
Shape into 8 to 10 cakes.
Fry in hot oil or shortening until lightly browned.
Drain on napkins.

title: christmas kringle
directions: Combine milk, yeast, 1 tablespoon sugar, egg yolks and cream in small bowl; mix well.
Let stand until foamy and proofed, about 10 minutes.
Blend flour, 1/4 cup sugar and salt in large mixing bowl. Cut in butter until pieces are about the size of small beans.
Fold in yeast mixture just until ingredients are moistened.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate 12 to 24 hours.

title: orange congealed salad
directions: Step 1:
Mix orange jello and add pineapple.
Let congeal, then sprinkle with a few chopped nuts.

title: chocolate fudge ice cream topping
directions: Mix butter and chips.
Add milk and sugar and bring to boil; boil for 7 to 8 minutes until thick, stirring constantly.
This can be reheated in microwave for hot fudge sundaes.
Sauce will keep for a long time.
Store in covered container in refrigerator.

title: creamed eggs with peas
directions: Cook peas as directed. Drain. Add eggs to cream sauce.
Heat. Add peas. Serve over noodles.
Yields 6 servings.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni without salt.
Drain well.
Combine with vegetables and toss well.
Stir in mayonnaise, basil and salt. Toss well.
Cover and chill 3 hours.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: fruit compote
directions: Mix; refrigerate 4 to 5 hours and enjoy.

title: chicken taco and rice
directions: Saute chicken in oil until opaque.
Add chicken broth, tomato sauce and taco seasoning mix.
Bring to a boil, then simmer, covered, 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add corn and peppers; bring to a full boil.
Stir in rice.
Cover and remove from heat; let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.
Serve with shredded cheese, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: broccoli and chicken
directions: Cook broccoli for a few minutes, and put on the bottom of a casserole dish.
Top with bite size pieces of the cooked chicken. Mix the cream of chicken soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder, pour this sauce over the chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle with the Cheddar cheese and top with the Ritz crackers.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pea salad
directions: Put in large bowl in layers.
Do not mix.

title: reese peanut butter cups
directions: You will also need Reese's cup or peanut shape molds and Reese's cup papers.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls flat in a 13 x 15-inch jelly roll pan. Bake as suggested on package until lightly browned.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese and all of the seasonings.
Spread over the cooled crust.
Then top with your favorite vegies, beginning with the chopped lettuce.
Grace suggests using tomatoes, green peppers, broccoli, cauliflower and shredded carrots.
Use your imagination. Pat veggies down.
Slice and serve.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix and roll into balls.
Dip each ball in a coating of:

title: rainbow delight
directions: Bake cake according to box directions.
Let cool.
Prepare jello according to box directions.
Poke holes throughout the cake with a fork.
Pour liquid jello into holes.
Top with Cool Whip. Chill before serving.
Enjoy!
Serves 10.

title: bing cherry salad
directions: Drain juice from cherries and pineapple (drain well).
Measure 1 1/2 cups juice and bring to a boil.
Pour over Jell-O; stir to dissolve.
Measure remainder of juice and water to make 1 1/2 cups.
Add to Jell-O.
Add fruits and stir well.
Pour into mold and chill until firm.

title: orange balls
directions: Roll wafers fine.
Mix all ingredients.
Make into small balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Do not bake.
Yield: 5 dozen.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Add flour to oil in preheated skillet or kettle cooker, on medium heat until it reaches a rich dark brown, stirring constantly to prevent scorching. Add remaining ingredients except shrimp. Seasoning to taste. Simmer for 30 minutes then add shrimp and cover; simmer for another 20 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: browen basil new potatoes
directions: Break green beans. Put them into pot. Wash them. Put them into pot. Put water and salt into pot. Put on stove for about 2 hours or until tender.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix powdered sugar and peanut butter into little balls. Spread onto crust.
Save some for the top.
Mix pudding as directed and spread on top of the sugar and peanut butter.
Spread 1 container of Cool Whip over the top.
Sprinkle the rest of the peanuts and sugar on the top.

title: refrigerator salad
directions: Mix dry gelatin and cottage cheese.
Add other ingredients. Mix and chill.
(Other flavors of gelatin may be used.) I serve this in sherbet dishes as a dessert.

title: lemon meringue
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl beat egg yolks; stir in sweetened condensed milk, ReaLemon and rind.
Pour in crust.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until foamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff, but not dry.
Spread meringue on top of pie; seal carefully to edge of crust.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until meringue is golden brown.

title: hamburger and potato casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Put 1/2 of hamburger in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with layer of thin sliced potatoes. Cover with hamburger, then put another layer of thin sliced potatoes on this.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour mushroom soup over all and top with cheese.

title: kate smith's supper salad
directions: Remove skin and bones from salmon and flake carefully.
Blend other ingredients and toss lightly.
Add salmon, mixing gently, just enough to blend in.

title: rigatoni
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and garlic.
Drain off fat.
Add sauce and simmer 30 minutes.
In buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, layer some of the cooked rigatoni noodles with Provolone as the next layer.
Spread 1 cup sour cream over Provolone and top with 1/2 the sauce.
Add another layer of rigatoni noodles, then Mozzarella and remainder of sauce.
Sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°, until bubbly.

title: campstove stew and dumplings
directions: In Dutch
oven	cook
and
stir meat until light brown; drain. Add
onion,
cabbage
and	celery; cook and stir until vegetables are
light	brown.	Stir
in tomatoes, kidney beans (with liquid), water and seasonings.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat;
simmer while preparing dough for dumplings.
Drop dough by spoonfuls onto simmering stew.
Cook uncovered 10 minutes; cover and cook 10 minutes longer.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Place a layer of broccoli and a layer of chicken pieces in casserole.
Sprinkle all over with garlic salt and chunks of butter.
Cover lightly with grated cheese.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Mix soup, sour cream, milk, cup of grated cheese and sherry together and heat.
Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle with almonds and paprika.
(Thinly sliced water chestnuts may be added.)
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: lasagna revisited
directions: Mix the cheeses, egg and parsley.
In boiling water with a little oil added, cook enough noodles to make three layers in a large 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Spray pan with Pam and put a layer of sauce in the bottom.
Put one layer of noodles.
Spread with half of the cheese mixture and sprinkle with half of the meat and mushrooms.
Repeat, starting with a generous layer of sauce.
Top with a layer of noodles, cover completely with a layer of sauce and sprinkle with generously with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Serve with more cheese and extra sauce, if desired.

title: south of the border special
directions: In skillet, brown beef, onion and garlic.
Drain off fat. Stir in water, tomato sauce, chili powder and oregano.
Pour half the mixture into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with half the beans and half the chips.
Repeat layering.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until heated.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: oven roasted potatoes
directions: In a large plastic bag or bowl, add all ingredients.
Close bag and shake, or toss in bowl until potatoes are evenly coated. Empty potatoes into a shallow casserole dish.
Bake, stirring occasionally, until golden brown or tender, at 450° for 40 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: louisiana style potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes; drain.
Slice into 1/4 inch slices.
Cut bacon into 1/2 inch pieces.
Fry until crisp; drain on paper towels, reserving 1 teaspoon drippings.
In small bowl combine salad dressing, hot sauce, pepper, bacon and drippings.
In large bowl combine potatoes, green pepper, onions and relish.
Add dressing and toss gently.
Cover and chill at least 4 hours.
To serve, spoon onto lettuce lined bowl.
Makes 8 servings.

title: campfire date loaf
directions: Blend all ingredients with just 1 cup of cracker crumbs.
Line bottom of loaf pan, 3 x 7 x 2 1/4-inch, with wax paper.
Then cover with remaining 1/4 cup crumbs.
Pack in blended mixture and chill several hours.

title: toffee cookie squares
directions: Cream together butter, shortening, brown sugar and egg yolk. Stir in vanilla, salt and flour.
Pat mixture into a 10 x 15 x 1-inch pan.
Bake in a slow oven (325°) for 15 to 20 minutes. Melt chocolate and spread over warm, baked mixture.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Cut into squares.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: cheese sauce
directions: In small bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Melt butter over medium heat in skillet.
Add dry ingredients a little at a time, mixing all the time.
Add milk a little at a time and stir until smooth.
Add cheese a little at a time and keep stirring until smooth.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and water.
Bring to a boil and cook until mixture spins a thread on a wooden spoon (about 5 minutes). Add raw peanuts and boil for 15 to 20 minutes on medium heat or until golden brown.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, salt and soda. Mix quickly and pour into two buttered cookie sheets and spread thin.
Cool and break into pieces.
Store in airtight containers.

title: swedish spice cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease baking sheets.
Set aside.
In large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Blend in egg and sour cream.
Stir in orange peel, cardamom, ginger and cloves.
Mix in flour and baking soda.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on prepared baking sheet.
Flatten each cookie with bottom of drinking glass.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until light golden brown.
Remove to cooling rack.
Makes 5 to 5 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: cobbler crust
directions: Combine all ingredients together and mix well.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch pan.
Add 3 cups of any canned fruit.
Pour over batter. Add 1 cup sugar and 1 cup of hot water.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes until lightly brown.
You can use rhubarb.
Cut back on sugar if you use peaches, apples or cherries.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water and salt until done.
Melt butter in 3-quart kettle.
Add carrots and onions; cover and cook until tender.
Remove from heat.
Blend in flour; stir in milk. Add 1/2 of potatoes.
Mash other 1/2 potatoes.
Add all ingredients; heat until steaming hot.
(Grated celery may be added, if you wish.)

title: chicken salad
directions: Cut deboned chicken into small chunks and place in large bowl. Cut grapes in half and place in bowl.
Add almonds, mayonnaise and sour cream.
Mix well.
Add seasoning salt and pepper.
Mix and serve.

title: ray's chili delight dip
directions: Spread Philly cheese in the bottom of 1 square baking dish; pour can of chili over top and sprinkle the Monterey cheese over top.
Bake at 350° until cheese on top is melted.
Serve hot with tostado chips and dip chips in mixture.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Split chiles.
Spread on bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Layer chiles and Cheddar cheese, chiles and Cheddar cheese.
Mix milk, eggs and seasonings and pour over cheese mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with tomato sauce, then Jack cheese.
Bake 15 more minutes until bubbly.
Great with green salad and French bread.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Cook cake according to package directions. Combine condensed milk and caramel. Punch holes in cake while warm and pour caramel mixture over cake. Top with Cool Whip and crushed candy bars.

title: beef tips
directions: Combine steak, undiluted soups and mushrooms in bowl. Mix well. Spoon into (greased) baking dish. Bake, covered, at 300° for 2 hours. Serve over hot cooked rice or noodles. Makes 8 servings.

title: waffles
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Set aside.
Beat egg yolks.
Add milk and beat. Add dry ingredients and beat.
Add vegetable oil and beat.
Fold in beaten egg whites. Cook on a hot waffle iron.
Add hickory nuts before cooking for a special treat.

title: cheryl's artichoke dip
directions: Drain and mash artichoke hearts; add other ingredients and mix together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with Wheat Triscuits or choice of crackers.

title: no-flip omelet
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
This can be prepared ahead and refrigerated, but allow 10 minutes for baking.
Double recipe for a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter; add sugar, cocoa, eggs, flour, baking powder, salt and vanilla.
Mix together and add chocolate chips and pecans.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: easy peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring sugar and milk to a boil until they reach the soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter.
Let stand to cool without stirring.
Once it cools, stir until mixture loses its glossy shine and begins to harden.
Quickly pour into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.

title: party mix
directions: Pour oil into oblong pan and mix other ingredients and put in oven at 200° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: marble pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 8 or 9-inch round cake pans.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with an electric mixer until creamy; gradually add sugars, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Stir in water and vanilla. Combine flour and next 3 ingredients; add to butter mixture, mixing well.
Stir in oats and remaining ingredients.
Drop batter by tablespoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Transfer cookies to wire racks to cool.
Yield:
8 dozen.

title: lime cooler
directions: Stir the sherbet to soften.
Stir in the remaining ingredients to blend.
Serves 4 glasses.
Other flavor sherbets can also be used.

title: boiled oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring first five ingredients to a boil for about 3 minutes. Remove from heat and add peanut butter, oats and vanilla.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Cut onions in quarters and slice very thin.
Set aside.
Melt 1/4 cup margarine or butter in saucepan and pour over stuffing. Mix thoroughly and line an 8-inch pie pan or 1-quart casserole dish with stuffing mixture.

title: sweet and crispy walnuts
directions: Heat the wok.
Add oil.
Deep fry the walnuts for about 1 minute. Remove and drain. Remove the oil from the wok and clean it.
Reheat the wok.

Place the walnuts and 1 tablespoon water in the wok. Stir lightly to moisten the walnuts. Add the powdered sugar. Stir to mix so that the nuts are lightly coated. Remove the walnuts and place them on a plate to cool. When cool, the sugar will become white and crispy.

title: open peach cake
directions: Melt butter, remove from heat; cool.
Mix the egg, sugar and vanilla in a mixing bowl; stir in butter.
Sift flour and baking powder together; stir into mixture until batter is fairly sticky. Place batter in oblong 7 x 12-inch baking dish.
Press dough with floured hands to fit bottom.
To skin peaches, place each in boiling water, remove immediately and peel.
Cut peaches into 1/2-inch wide pieces and arrange overlapping on top of dough; pressing in slightly.
When dough is entirely covered with peach slices, sprinkle sugar over liberally.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pepper steak
directions: In skillet, melt margarine. Add beef; sprinkle with garlic powder and saute, stirring slightly, until browned. Add onion, tomatoes and bouillon cube. Blend together cornstarch, water, soy sauce, sugar and salt. Stir into meat mixture.
Add green peppers. Simmer about 45 minutes.
Serve with rice or whipped potatoes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Grease a baking dish.
Line baking dish with tortillas.
Save remainder to add in layers.
Mix together the soups, tomatoes, peppers, onion, 1/2 of cheese and chicken.
Pour in dish in layers, using remaining tortillas.
Top with sour cream.
Add remaining cheese; top with olives.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and Lipton soup mix.
Line bottom of casserole dish with meat.
Mix the two soups together and pour over meat.
Continue to layer meat and soup.
Top layer is Tater Tots.
Cook at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: gingered fruit salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine first four ingredients.
In a small jar, stir together remaining ingredients.
Pour over fruits, tossing to blend.
Cover and refrigerate 4 to 8 hours.
Yields 8 servings.

title: chocolate wafer torte
directions: Crush chocolate wafers and place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Save some for topping.
Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water. Separate eggs.
Beat yolks with 1/2 cup sugar and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Scald milk; add to yolk mixture.
Return to stove and cook slowly until mixture coats a spoon.
While hot, add gelatin and stir until dissolved.
When cool, add 3 beaten egg whites, 1 cup whipped cream and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour over crushed wafers. Sprinkle with remaining wafers.
Set in refrigerator to cool.

title: whole wheat banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Stir in banana and pecans.
Spoon batter into a greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until a wooden pick comes out clean.
Cool in pan 5 minutes. Remove to a wire rack and cool completely.

title: hoagie sandwiches
directions: Prepare steaks according to package.
While steaks are cooking, spread the spaghetti sauce on the loaves.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Add other ingredients according to taste.
Add steaks. Put in microwave for 4 to 5 minutes.
Add chips to complete a meal. That took less than 30 minutes to prepare.

title: sugar and spice nuts
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, melt butter; stir in nuts and 1/2 cup sugar.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until sugar melts and nuts brown, about 8 to 12 minutes.
In large bowl, mix other ingredients; stir in caramelized nuts.
Cool completely on wax paper.
When cool, break apart into individual pieces.
This makes 3 cups.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Serve on tossed salad, coleslaw, potato salad, etc.

title: butterscotch-oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugars.
Add egg and water. Sift flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Stir in vanilla, butterscotch chips, nuts and oatmeal.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 6 to 7 dozen.

title: cranberry sauce jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add cold water and let set until it begins to thicken.
Drain pineapple and add to the Jell-O.
Add cranberry sauce and nuts.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: lime cornish hens
directions: Thaw hens.
Make stuffing mix.
Spoon into hens.
Mix butter with sugar, lime juice, wine and soy sauce.
Brush hens with sauce.
Place trivet in slow cooker.
Place hens on end, neck down.
Cover and cook on low for 5 to 7 hours.
Brush with soy sauce once during cooking, if possible.

title: slaw
directions: Mix well and let set 4 or 5 hours.
Mix several times more. Keeps about 2 weeks.

title: taco puffs
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Prepare seasoning packet as per instructions on package.
Roll out biscuit and fill with beef and cheddar cheese.
Top with another biscuit and seal edges.
Repeat until all biscuits are used.
Bake in oven for 15 minutes or until biscuit has turned golden brown.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Follow directions regarding thawing and rising of bread.
Roll out each loaf of bread separately.
Roll as thin as possible. Brush bread with egg.
Then sprinkle Italian seasoning over bread. Place 1/2 of pepperoni on bread.
Sprinkle on Mozzarella cheese. Roll bread tightly.
Repeat on other loaf.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
May be frozen for later use.

title: chicken amore
directions: Coat chicken with flour, salt and pepper.
Fry chicken in olive oil and brown.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Simmer on low for 30 minutes.
Serve over buttered noodles.

title: shrimp fritters
directions: Salt and pepper shrimp.
Set aside and prepare batter.

title: sausage stew
directions: The amount of each item depends on the number of people you hope to feed.
I generally use more sausage and potatoes, less celery and onions (i.e., 1 cup sausage, 1 cup potatoes, 1/2 cup celery and 1/2 cup onions.
Adjust to your own taste.)

title: homemade chili
directions: Cook meat until done.
Cook all other ingredients in large pot.
Add meat and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes. Serve hot!

title: shrimp-crab casserole #2
directions: Combine all ingredients, Mix well.
Place in buttered 9 x 13 dish.
Bake 350 for 35 minutes.
Serves 8 - 10.

title: fort worth dip
directions: In a small bowl, combine all ingredients listed. Chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease and flour pan well.
Add nuts and coconut in bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Pour over top of nuts and coconut.

title: golden corn bread
directions: Combine corn meal, flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add milk, egg and melted shortening.
Beat until smooth.
Bake in greased 8-inch square baking dish in preheated hot oven at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes approximately 9 servings.

title: whipped cream pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together, then add eggs, one at a time, then add cream and flour alternately.
Bake in a tube or loaf pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: spanish flan
directions: Make the cheese soft by mixing the can of condensed milk with the cheese mashed with a fork.
Add the regular milk.
Pour in a blender; add eggs.
Mix well.
Add bread; mix again.
Pour into a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 45 to 50 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Blend sugar, spices and salt together.
Beat eggs with milk and combine with sugar mixture.
Add this mixture to beaten sweet potatoes and heat in medium saucepan until almost boiling.
Remove from heat and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue to bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Makes 8 servings.

title: scalloped potatoes and pork chops
directions: Combine celery soup, water, sour cream, onion soup mix, salt and pepper.
Place potatoes in greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish. Pour mixture over potatoes.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hawaiian delights
directions: In a large mixer bowl, cream together sugars and margarine until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Stir together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Stir in oats, candy and coconut.
Using a tablespoon, roll mixture into 1-inch balls. Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove and cool on wire rack. Yield: 6 dozen cookies.

title: salted nut rolls
directions: Melt peanut butter chips, sweetened condensed milk, margarine and marshmallows.
Spread melted mixture over peanuts and put remaining peanuts on top.
Refrigerate, then serve.

title: thousand dollar orange salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add 7-Up; refrigerate about 45 minutes or until slightly jelled.
Whip cream until stiff.
Fold whipping cream and remaining ingredients into jello mixture.
Refrigerate until firm.
Serve.

title: ranchers supreme
directions: Brown meat and onions; drain.
Place meat mixture in 8-inch casserole.
Pour soup over meat; top with cheese.
Cover with Tater Tots and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 450° until Tater Tots are browned.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: ever ready hamburger mix
directions: Cook and stir beef over medium heat until brown and meat is separated.
Add onion and cook gently until soft but not brown. Stir in remaining ingredients and simmer, uncovered, until thick. Spoon off any excess fat.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Melt butter; add flour and pecans (1 cup).
Stir well.
Press into a 9 x 12-inch pan; bake 25 minutes at 350° or until golden brown.
Set aside to cool.

title: dust pan pie
directions: Mix frozen potatoes, meat and soup.
Spoon into pie shell. Bake at 400° for about 30 minutes, until bubbly.
May also top with shredded cheese of choice prior to baking.

title: micro chicken casserole
directions: In small bowl place soup, onion and water.
Stir until blended. Peel tomatoes and slice thin.
In casserole layer 1/2 corn chips. Top with 1 can chicken, then half of tomatoes.
Pour 1/2 soup mixture over.
Repeat layer in same order.
Microwave at Full power for 15 minutes.

title: pepper pork chops
directions: Combine all ingredients except pork chops.
Brush chops well with marinade.
Cover; set aside for 30 minutes, brushing occasionally with marinade.
Place chops on grill 5 to 6 inches above medium coals; reserve marinade.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes on each side.
Brush chops with marinade and grill an additional 10 to 12 minutes, brushing occasionally with marinade.

title: sweet and sour vegetable salad
directions: Mix first six ingredients together.
Combine rest of ingredients to make dressing for salad.
Pour dressing over salad.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Microwave chocolate chips and 14 oz. almond bark on high for 2 minutes. Stir and microwave an additional 1-2 minutes. Stir in marshmallows, cereal, and peanuts. Pour onto greased pizza pan. Top with cherries, coconut. Microwave 2 oz. almond bark and oil one minute and stir. Drizzle melted almond bark over toppings. Refrigerate. Cut into wedges.

title: creamed potato soup
directions: Cut potatoes and onions into eighths.
Coarsely chop green onions.
Add along with the garlic to the butter in a heavy 3-quart saucepan.
Add onion to butter and saute for 1 minute. Add the potatoes and pour in the broth.
Simmer for 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Pour soup in food processor or blender in batches.
Add cream, milk, salt, pepper and nutmeg to soup. Chill if served cold.

title: horseradish salad
directions: Sprinkle both packages of gelatin over boiling water and stir until dissolved. Add cottage cheese and mayonnaise.
Mix well. When salad begins to set, add pineapple and horseradish.
Serves 6 to 8 people.
Prepare the day before.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large bowl, mix the soup, mayonnaise, egg, onion and cheese with the cooked and drained eggplant. Put mixture in a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish and cover with cracker crumbs; dot with butter. Bake for 25 minutes.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix together. Make small meatballs.

title: chicken spaghetti #1
directions: Cook spaghetti in chicken broth.
Do not drain.
Add all other ingredients and toss until well mixed.
Turn into greased casserole and bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: impossible peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Form into small balls.
Dip into sugar, place on cookie sheet.
Press with fork to flatten. Bake 15 minutes at 325°.
Leave on cookie sheet for 5 minutes to hold together.

title: sweet pickles from dill
directions: Drain off brine from pickles.
Rinse with cold water.
Slice pickles into strips.
Repack into jar and pour the other ingredients over the pickles.
Cap securely and place in refrigerator.
Turn frequently, making sure that the sugar dissolves.
Serve after at least 24 hours of refrigeration.

title: corn pudding
directions: To the corn add flour, milk, and melted butter.
Next the well beaten eggs, salt and cayenne. Lastly add the baking powder. Put into a greased 2 quart baking dish.
Bake in a slow oven until firm and brown, 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve at once in its baking dish.
Serves 8.

title: "mammie starks strawberry jam"
directions: Clean grapes.
Place in saucepan over medium heat; do not stir. Cook until grapes are tender and juice forms; strain for jelly and put pulp through colander for marmalade.

title: old-fashioned custard pie
directions: Beat the whole eggs until thoroughly mixed.
Then add the milk; gradually fold in the sugar, then add salt and flavoring and continue to mix until sugar is dissolved.
Pour the egg mixture into the unbaked 9-inch pie shell (deep dish).
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour or until custard is brown.

title: poppy seed ham biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients together; spread on both sides of rolls and add slices of ham.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Boil and drain the cabbage. Mix the cream cheese, soup, mushrooms and almonds. Mix together and put in buttered casserole. Add buttered crumbs or Ritz crackers (crushed) over the top. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: honeybunch munchies
directions: Mix together oats, coconut, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Cook butter, sugar and honey until sugar dissolves.
Pour over oat mixture.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° in a 13 x 9-inch pan; cook until brown.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix all together, then add nuts.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes.

title: strawberry jello cream salad
directions: Make jello according to package directions.
(Don't use speed-set method).
Make jello in a large casserole dish.
When jello has slightly thickened, fold in rest of ingredients.
May either use the cherries in the mixture or sprinkle as a garnish on top.
Will have to chill for several hours before jello has set.

title: blueberry dumplings
directions: Sugar blueberries with juice to taste.
Bring to a boil in a skillet.
Mix dumpling recipe on Bisquick box.
Drop onto boiling blueberries.
Follow directions on Bisquick box for cooking.

title: wet crust shoo-fly pie
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar and shortening.
Reserve 3/4 cup of mixture for topping.

title: crock-pot meat loaf
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients except the 2 tablespoons syrup and 2 tablespoons catsup.
Shape into a round loaf and place in crock-pot.
Combine the 2 tablespoons catsup and corn syrup; spread over meat loaf for glaze.
Cook on auto for 4 hours; low for 5 to 6 hours or high for 3 hours.

title: baked manicotti
directions: Cook shells.
Add oil to water.
Brown chuck and drain.
Salt and pepper.
Beat eggs and add all cheeses.
Cook spinach and drain.
Add to cheese mixture.
Cut slit all the way down shell. Fill and put slit side down in dish.
Add sauce and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°, covered with foil. Uncover and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cook 10 minutes.

title: italian spaghetti
directions: Brown hamburger and onion. Add tomato juice, mushrooms, green pepper and spices. Thicken with cornstarch if needed. When heated thoroughly pour over cooked noodles of choice.

title: potato salad dressing
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in medium saucepan until blended.
Add milk.
Cook until it thickens, stirring constantly.
Cool 15 minutes.
Add salad dressing.
Pour over potatoes while still warm.

title: broiled beef pul ko-kee
directions: Cut the beef into thin slices 3-inch squares. Add sugar and oil.
Mix
well.
Combine soy sauce, pepper, chopped onion (including	top),
chopped	garlic, prepared sesame and flour. Add to the
meat. Mix well.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Broil on a charcoal fire or
fry
in
a small amount of oil until tender. If frying meat, cover tightly after it is well browned.
Add a small amount
of	water
and steam until meat is tender. Serve hot.

title: true blue cheese
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Yields 1-1/2 cups of dressing.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Combine squash and water in a 1-quart saucepan.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain and mash squash.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix until smooth.
Add flour sifted with soda, baking powder and salt. Add oats, rice cereal and coconut.
Mold into balls the size of walnut.
Press flat with a fork.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 5 to 6 dozen cookies.

title: rouladin
directions: Pound steak 1/4-inch thick.
Cut in half; season.
Saute bacon until not quite crisp and chop.
Dice onion; top each steak piece with bacon and onion and season.
Roll up and fasten with toothpicks to hold.
Brown rolls in margarine or canola oil until brown.
Add bouillon and wine or water just to cover.
Simmer gently 1 1/2 hours.
Remove rolls and thicken gravy.

title: overnight cabbage salad
directions: Shred cabbage and chop other vegetables fine. Put in large bowl (glass or plastic) mixing all together well. Put other ingredients in sauce pan, mix and bring to a boil. Pour over vegetables and mix well. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: squash
directions: Salt squash to taste.
Mix first 3 ingredients.
Fold in egg whites.
Lay 1/2 of the squash, egg mixture and cheese in a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Crumble bacon and sprinkle on top of that and repeat layers.
Mix butter and crumbs and sprinkle on top of that.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: rhubarb crumble
directions: Spread rhubarb on bottom of 9 x 13 pan.
Mix sugar, eggs and 4 Tbsp. flour together and pour over rhubarb.
Mix 2 cups flour, brown sugar, soda and butter to crumble.
Top rhubarb with crumble mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: italian oyster crackers
directions: Spray 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan with nonstick spray.
Spread crackers and then spray with nonstick spray.
Sprinkle with Italian seasoning and garlic powder.
Toss to coat.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes, stirring once.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cool completely. Store in tightly covered container.
Makes 6 cups.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 300° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours until firm.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add vanilla and milk.
Add dry ingredients, mixing well.
Add oatmeal.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet sprayed with no-stick spray.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: pear-pecan bread
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add flour, cinnamon and buttermilk. Stir in pears, pecans and vanilla. Pour into a greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs well, add sugar and mix.
Add rest of ingredients mixing well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° until golden brown.

title: dirt dessert
directions: In mixing bowl, beat oleo, cream cheese, powdered sugar and cookie cream; set aside.
Whip milk and dry pudding.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Add first cream mix.
Crumble Oreo cookies.
Put in an 8 to 10-inch flowerpot or sand pail.
Place layer of crumbs, then layer of pudding mix.
End with crumbs on top.
Garnish with gummy worms and decorate with plastic or silk flowers.
Use shovel to serve.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in an airtight jar. To serve, place 2 tablespoons of mix in a large mug.
Stir in boiling water (1 cup of water).

title: shrimp salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water. Add lemon juice.
Let stand and then beat until fluffy. Add the remaining ingredients. Chill until firm.
You can also use salmon instead of shrimp.

title: corn relish
directions: Mix corn, onions and bell peppers.
Add pimentos.
Combine rest of ingredients and pour over corn mixture.
Put in a large pan and bring to a boil.
Simmer on low until onions and peppers are tender (about 30 minutes).
Put in sterile jars and seal.

title: broken window glass pie
directions: Prepare the 3 flavors of jello separately, using 1 cup boiling water and 1/2 cup cold water each.
Pour each flavor into an 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm or overnight.
Then combine lemon jello, sugar and one cup boiling water, stir until jello and sugar are dissolved.
Stir in pineapple juice.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Meanwhile, mix the graham cracker crumbs and melted margarine.
Press into the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Cut the firm jello into 1/2-inch cubes.
Blend Cool Whip in the lemon jello.
Fold in jello cubes.
Pour into graham cracker-lined dish.
Chill at least 5 hours.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: pizza with lox
directions: Knead ready made pizza dough on a floured board and spread it out to a large circle.
Smear olive oil on a 14-inch flat pan and spread out the dough in the pan.
Pour sauce over the dough.
Then sprinkle the Mozzarella and the tablespoon of olive oil on the dough.
Place the pieces of lox on top and sprinkle on the oregano. Bake the pizza in an oven for 15 to 20 minutes at 450°.

title: corn and green bean casserole
directions: Mix corn, green beans, mushroom soup, sour cream and cheese together.
Put into deep square casserole dish.
Melt one stick oleo and mix with crumbled crackers; add to top of casserole. Bake at 375° to 400° until brown or it bubbles around edges.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Add dry gelatin to cake mix.
Add water and oil; beat well. Beat in eggs.
Fold in strawberries.
Pour into a greased and floured pan that has been lined with waxed paper.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: marvelous "super" salad
directions: Layer ingredients.
Add 2 cups buttermilk dressing.
Garnish with 1 egg and part of the cheese.
Let set awhile before serving.

title: barbecue baked beans
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine all ingredients and top with bacon.
Bake, uncovered, for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecue meat loaf
directions: Mix together beef, crumbs, onion, egg, salt, pepper and 1/4 can tomato sauce. Form into loaf and put in shallow pan. Combine rest of ingredients. Pour over loaf. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: lemon bars
directions: In medium bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups flour and confectioners sugar; cut into margarine until crumbly.
Press onto bottom of lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan; bake 15 minutes at 350°. In a large bowl, combine eggs, granulated sugar, 3 tablespoons flour, baking powder and ReaLemon juice; mix well.
Pour over crust.
Bake 20 minutes or until golden.
Cool.
Cut into bars. Store covered in refrigerator; serve at room temperature.

title: diet salad
directions: Mix oranges, pineapple and cottage cheese.
Sprinkle dry jello over mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: irish stew
directions: Heat fat in a large skillet.
Roll beef in flour and brown well in the hot fat; add enough water to cover and cook covered over low heat for 40 minutes, then add diced vegetables.
Mix well and add enough water to cover and cook covered slowly 40 minutes. Makes 4 generous servings.

title: snicker squares
directions: Melt butter and caramels over medium-low heat, stirring constantly. Add chocolate and marshmallows; stir until melted. Add peanuts and mix well. Pour into buttered 9 x 13 pan. Cool completely and cut.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend first 2 ingredients, then stir in flour.
Chill slightly (about 1 hour), then shape into 2 dozen 1-inch balls.
Flatten into ungreased muffin tins.
Beat next 5 ingredients until mixed well, then fold in the pecans.
Fill to 2/3 full in each muffin cup.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: microwave corn-on-the-cob
directions: Cut ends from corn.
Do not shuck!
Microwave 6 to 8 minutes on High.
Test for doneness.
May need a minute or 2 more. Remove.
Shuck and remove silks.
Butter, salt and eat!

title: hearty goulash
directions: Saute hamburger, onion, green pepper, garlic and mushrooms in olive oil.
Cook noodles separately in saucepan.
Add noodles and rest of ingredients to hamburger mixture.
Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Procedure:
Wash tomatoes.
Remove stems and trim off bruised or discolored portions.
To prevent juice from separating, quickly cut about 1 pound of fruit into quarters and put directly into a saucepan.
Heat immediately to boiling while crushing.
Continue to slowly add and crush freshly cut tomato quarters.
Make sure the mixture boils constantly and vigorously while you add the remaining tomatoes.
Simmer five minutes after you add all pieces.

title: old-fashion potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes; remove skins and slice into a large bowl.
In a medium size bowl, mix the remainder of ingredients.
Mix well and pour over potatoes; toss and add chopped parsley.
Serve warm or cold.
It is best to make ahead of time so all flavors can draw into the potatoes.

title: stuffed tomato salad
directions: Scald tomatoes in hot water and then remove thin skins.
Scoop out center pulp and seeds, reserving all.
Turn tomatoes upside down to drain.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in casserole dish, sprayed with Pam.
Cut up onions on top of chicken.
Season with onion powder, garlic powder, oregano and a splash of lemon juice.
Pour wine over chicken.
Cook in 325° oven for 40 minutes and check, could need a little longer.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Stir the milk, sugar and salt until sugar dissolves and mixture boils.
Cook slowly, without stirring, until mixture forms soft ball in cold water. Add the peanut butter and vanilla without stirring. Cool until lukewarm.
Beat until thick.
Pour into buttered pan. Cool. Cut into squares.

title: chess pie(makes two)
directions: Cream all ingredients, except milk and vanilla.
Add the milk and vanilla.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then for 30 to 40 minutes at 325°.

title: icebox refrigerator cookies
directions: Mix together well the sugars, shortening and eggs. Add dry ingredients with nuts and divide dough into 2 pieces. Make long rolls; wrap in waxed paper and refrigerate overnight. Slice cookies 1/4-inch thick and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Pinch cake into small pieces.
Prepare pudding according to directions.
Layer ingredients in bottom of punch bowl in order listed using 1/2 of each.
Repeat. Refrigerate.

title: sugar coated walnuts
directions: Mix above ingredients together in saucepan and bring to a hard boil.
Boil until mixture starts to string when poured from a spoon.

title: saucy apple swirl cake
directions: Combine dry cake mix, eggs and applesauce; beat well.
Pour 1/2 cake batter into greased angel food pan.
Mix together the cinnamon and sugar; sprinkle over the batter in the pan.
Add balance of cake batter.
Bake according to cake mix directions.
Serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: breaded pork chops
directions: Season pork chops with salt and pepper.
Cover with corn flake crumbs.
Dip in combined eggs and milk and again in crumbs.
Heat Presto cooker and add shortening; brown chops on both sides.
Add water; close cover.
Place pressure gauge and cook 12 minutes with pressure up.
Let pressure drop at will.

title: rafus' cajun rice
directions: Brown ground chuck and sausage in a pan, then drain.
Pour uncooked rice into a long casserole dish.
Add ground chuck, sausage and soups, then mix together well.
Set oven to 375°.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and margarine.
Stir well.
Add eggs and beat with mixer for 2 1/2 minutes.
Add salt, milk and vanilla.
Stir in pecans, if desired.
Pour filling into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: 4 bean salad
directions: Drain beans and add remaining ingredients carefully. Refrigerate overnight.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Turn into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Melt 1/2 cup butter; blend in flour.
Add chicken bouillon.
Cook over low heat.
Gradually add milk.
Cook until thick and pour over broccoli.
Heat 2/3 cup cold water and 6 tablespoons butter and pour over stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pear relish
directions: Wash first 5 ingredients in cold water.
Peel and core the pears.
Remove stem and seeds from the peppers.
Clean the celery, peel the onion and put them through a food chopper.
Then add sugar, salt, vinegar and allspice.
Mix and let stand overnight. Pack in preheated jars.
Process 20 minutes in hot water bath at simmering temperature.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
In large skillet, add ground beef and onion on medium heat until the ground beef is done.
Drain well. Add green chilies and corn.
In a medium bowl, add tomato sauce and enchilada sauce mix well.
Add the sauce to the meat mixture. Heat through.
In a casserole dish, put some tortilla chips on the bottom, some of the meat mixture and some of the cheeses.
Repeat the layer.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Serve with salsa and sour cream. Serves 6.

title: 3 meat baked beans
directions: Brown
ground
beef, onions and bell pepper together and drain.
Brown
franks
lightly.
Fry
bacon until crisp. (Crumble.)	Mix
remaining	ingredients together.
Add ground chuck, onions,
peppers and franks.
Mix and pour into casserole dish. Top with bacon crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cheesy barbecue wraps
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add barbecue sauce, onion and green pepper.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in Velveeta.
Fill rolls with meat mixture.
Wrap in foil.
Bake at 300° for 10 minutes.

title: chicken stuffing casserole
directions: Butter 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put 1/2 of stuffing on bottom.
Add beans.
Sprinkle 1/2 of almonds.
Cover with chicken.

title: no peek stew
directions: Put all ingredients in Dutch oven.
Cover tightly with foil. Place lid over foil.
Bake 3 hours in a 300° oven.
No peeking.

title: margaret's cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan. (Roll out corn flakes to crush.)
Mix corn flakes and melted butter together. Put over top of mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Mix together:
chicken, Veg-all and soups.
Pour into a buttered 9x13-inch casserole dish.
Dot top with butter.
Put separated crescent rolls on top like a crust.

title: one step pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Stir
in sugar, corn syrup, melted margarine and pecans.
Pour in
a
9-inch shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
It will	be done when firm and puffy in the middle.

title: crock-pot barbecue stew
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Combine all ingredients in a large crock-pot and cook for 8 hours.

title: dairy meat casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and green pepper; add tomato sauce and seasoning.
In bowl, combine cream cheese, sour cream, cottage cheese and olives (mix in blender or mix well).
Line casserole dish with half of cooked noodles.
Spread with cheese next.
Cover with noodles.
Top with meat.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: date roll
directions: Combine granulated sugar and milk in saucepan and boil to soft ball stage.
Add dates and let melt or cook slowly for about 5 minutes.
Remove from stove and add butter; beat.
Add walnuts and finish beating until stiff.
Turn out on wet cloth and roll up like sausage.
When cool, shape it so it will be round and let it lay in wet cloth until cold.
Then slice and cover both sides with powdered sugar.

title: christmas fondue
directions: Melt chocolate over low heat.
Add all ingredients, mixing well!
Use angel food bite size cake, apples and any thing!

title: frito-bean casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except Fritos.
Simmer about 15 minutes.

title: egg foo yong
directions: Prepare mix according to package directions.
Beat eggs with soy sauce, salt and pepper.
Stir in cooled rice mixture, bean sprouts
and
sliced
onions.
Drop
by
cupfuls on greased griddle.
Brown on each side.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Blend mashed sweet potatoes with other ingredients.
Bake in 2-quart casserole for about 35 minutes.

title: baked squash
directions: Cut squash into 2-inch chunks.
Boil squash or microwave until just tender.
Place squash in colander and mash as much water as possible from squash.
Let drain 10 minutes.

title: microwave caramel popcorn
directions: You will need 1 large brown paper bag and wax paper.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add egg and vanilla. Blend in flour; mix well. Refrigerate 2 hours.
Roll out dough on floured and sugared surface. Cut out cookies.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 9 minutes. Frost with powdered sugar frosting.

title: ploughman's lunch
directions: All of the ingredients are per person.
Serve on 1 large plate.
Let each person break their own bread and add appropriate amount of items per mouthful.
Fun to serve.
Fun to eat.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar. Add vanilla and food coloring; mix well. Add eggs and cream well. Sift and measure flour with cocoa. Sift 3 times and add to mixture alternately with buttermilk. Last, fold in soda mixed with vinegar. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool.

title: springtime jello
directions: Mix sugar and pineapple together.
Bring to a boil and simmer 10 minutes with a lid on.
Take lid off and let stand to cool.

title: macaroni vegetable medley
directions: In medium saucepan, cook macaroni to desired doneness as directed on package.
Drain and rinse with hot water.
Return to saucepan; keep warm.
Meanwhile, cook vegetables and sauce pouches as directed in package.
Add contents of both pouches and dill weed to macaroni; toss to combine well.
Spoon into serving bowl; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: pickled onions
directions: Peel onions (better make this a family project since it's such a dull chore) and cover with boiling water.
Drain.
Then put into ice water to cool and crispen.
Cut red and green peppers into strips.

title: southern gal biscuits(arkansas best)
directions: Sift or mix flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and cream of tartar into bowl.
Add shortening to flour mixture.
Blend together.
Pour milk into flour mixture slowly.
Add egg.
Stir to a stiff dough.
Knead 5 times.
Roll to a 1/2-inch thickness. Cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: tuna-cheese biscuit bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Arrange biscuits in an ungreased 9-inch square or 12 x 8-inch pan.
In mixing bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake, uncovered, 25 to 30 minutes or until biscuits have risen to the top and are well-browned.
Serves 4 to 6.
Serve immediately.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all together and let set in refrigerator overnight.
Good served with variety of raw vegetables.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli and chicken.
Arrange in a 9 x 13-inch pan all of broccoli.
Cover with good size pieces of cooked chicken. Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry.
Spread sauce over chicken.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken salad amandine
directions: Boil chicken breasts in lightly salted water until tender. Let chicken cool.
Separate meat and cut in medium-size strips. Toss remaining ingredients, except almonds, with chicken meat. Cover and refrigerate until serving time.
Garnish with almonds and serve.

title: cream puffs
directions: Heat milk and butter.
Bring these ingredients to the boiling point.
Add the sifted flour and salt.
Cook and stir the batter until it leaves the sides of the pan and forms a ball.
Remove it from the fire.
Beat in, one at a time, the eggs.
Be careful to beat 1 egg until well blended before adding the next.
Place spoonfuls of batter on a cooking sheet.
Heap it well in the middle.
Allow 2 inches between the puffs.
Bake in a hot 375° oven for 20 minutes.
Reduce the heat to 350° and bake them 5 minutes longer.
Test the puffs by removing one from the oven.
If it does not fall, it is thoroughly done.
When the puffs are cooled, cut almost in half and fill with whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Put chocolate icing on top.

title: red rosies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store in airtight container.
Use 2 heaping teaspoonfuls of mix to a cup of hot water.

title: brown sugar pies
directions: Double for 3 pies.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in flat pyrex baking dish.
Mix soup, chestnuts, sour cream and half of poppy seed.
Pour over chicken; crumble crackers and spread butter over crackers.
Sprinkle the rest of poppy seed.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: downy cushion rolls
directions: Scald milk; add sugar, salt and soft yeast.
Cool until lukewarm.
Add 2 cups flour.
Mix in eggs.
Beat until smooth. Add remaining flour.
Let rise to double in size.
Stir down; let rise.
Roll out on board.
Cut into rolls.
Let rise.
Bake in hot oven.

title: chocolate pudding pops
directions: In saucepan, stir together pudding mix, milk, sugar, and salt until smooth. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil. Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice. Pour into 4 popsicle molds and cool 15 minutes. Insert popsicle sticks and freeze hard. Remove pops from molds. Serve or wrap in plastic and store in freezer.

title: sweet meatballs
directions: In a saucepan, add these ingredients.
Heat until smooth and melted.
Pour over meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cherry lemonade
directions: Combine lemon juice and sugar; stir until sugar dissolves. Cover and chill.
Stir in mineral water.
Serve over ice.
If desired, garnish with lemon slices and cherries.

title: sweet aspic(good for parties!)
directions: Dissolve jello	in
boiling
water.
Add
can of tomato soup and vinegar.
Fill	your
favorite ring mold with chopped celery and egg.
Pour
the
jello mixture over them.
Set on a pie pan and put in refrigerator to solidify.
Unmold.

title: annie's favorite salad
directions: Toss ingredients and serve chilled.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Fry bacon and crumble.
Mix everything together.
Put in crock-pot on low heat for about 4 hours.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Prepare shells; drain.
Mix shells and next 6 ingredients. In small bowl, mix mayonnaise, horseradish and season salt.
Add to salad mixture; toss.
Cover; chill.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: peanut butter bonbons
directions: Melt margarine and peanut butter together.
Add powdered sugar and mix well.
Then add Rice Krispies and mix well.
Shape into round balls.
Refrigerate about 30 to 45 minutes.
Then put a toothpick in each one and dip into chocolate mixture.

title: southern potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes, then chop and set to the side.
Put onions and celery stalks in a pot and boil until tender with a small amount of water.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in large bowl and let set overnight in the refrigerator.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients.
Spread in pan.
Bake until golden brown, about 25 minutes.
Cut into pieces.
